sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost
from 
  partsupp
where partsupp.ps_comment is NULL
limit 156;

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty
from 
  partsupp
where partsupp.ps_supplycost is NULL;
nl: What are the part-supplier combinations with no supply cost?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as tid) as tid))
from 
  supplier
where supplier.s_nationkey is not NULL
limit 104;
nl: What are the supplier IDs, comments, and addresses of suppliers with a nation key, along with any additional information?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey
from 
  partsupp
where partsupp.ps_supplycost > partsupp.ps_supplycost
limit 143;
nl: What are the part-supplier combinations with unique supply costs that exceed themselves?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  lineitem.l_tax, 
  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  lineitem.l_shipmode, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as xid8) as xid8)), 
  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  lineitem.l_shipmode
from 
  lineitem
where lineitem.l_linenumber < lineitem.l_linenumber
limit 108;
nl: What are the ship dates and details for all orders that have incomplete shipping instructions?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_comment
from 
  nation
    inner join nation
      inner join nation
      on (nation.n_comment = nation.n_comment )
    on (nation.n_nationkey is not NULL)
where nation.n_comment is not NULL
limit 101;
nl: What are the details of each nation, including its key and comment, where the nation has a comment?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  lineitem.l_tax, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  region.r_name, 
  supplier.s_name, 
  region.r_name, 
  region.r_comment, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  lineitem.l_extendedprice
from 
  region
    inner join lineitem
      inner join supplier
      on (lineitem.l_tax = supplier.s_acctbal )
    on (lineitem.l_receiptdate <= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
where lineitem.l_partkey <= region.r_regionkey
limit 126;
nl: What are the receipt dates, taxes, and comments for suppliers who have a certain account balance, along with the names of their regions, addresses, and extended prices?

sql:
select  
  part.p_comment
from 
  part
where part.p_container is not NULL
limit 78;
nl: What are the comments for parts that have a container?

sql:
select  
  part.p_mfgr, 
  part.p_type, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  part.p_brand, 
  part.p_comment, 
  part.p_retailprice, 
  part.p_mfgr, 
  part.p_mfgr, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as date) as date)), 
  part.p_name
from 
  part
where part.p_type is NULL
limit 66;
nl: What are the manufacturer, type, maximum value, brand, comment, retail price, and name of parts that have no specific type, along with their earliest available date?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey
from 
  partsupp
    inner join nation
    on (partsupp.ps_availqty = nation.n_nationkey )
where nation.n_regionkey is not NULL;

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_linestatus
from 
  lineitem
where lineitem.l_comment is not NULL
limit 121;
nl: What are the l_linestatus values for orders with comments, and how many of them are there?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  orders.o_orderkey, 
  supplier.s_acctbal
from 
  lineitem
    inner join orders
        inner join region
          inner join orders
            inner join part
            on (orders.o_custkey = part.p_partkey )
          on (part.p_size <= region.r_regionkey)
        on (part.p_retailprice = orders.o_totalprice)
      inner join supplier
      on (orders.o_totalprice < orders.o_totalprice)
    on (lineitem.l_quantity is not NULL)
where orders.o_clerk <= lineitem.l_shipinstruct;
nl: What are the return flags, order keys, and account balances for suppliers where the total price of an order matches the retail price of a part, considering only regions with sizes that match the size of parts?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  supplier.s_name
from 
  supplier
where supplier.s_suppkey < supplier.s_nationkey;
nl: What are the details of suppliers whose key is less than their nation key?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_linestatus
from 
  nation
    inner join lineitem
      inner join nation
      on (nation.n_nationkey >= lineitem.l_suppkey)
    on (nation.n_name is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_shipmode <= nation.n_name
limit 107;
nl: What are the statuses of all orders shipped by each supplier, grouped by the mode used for shipping?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_returnflag
from 
  lineitem
where lineitem.l_quantity is not NULL;
nl: What return flags are associated with non-null quantities?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey
from 
  partsupp
where partsupp.ps_supplycost is not NULL
limit 87;
nl: What are the comments, supply costs, and keys for non-null supply costs in the parts supplier table?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_custkey
from 
  lineitem
          inner join customer
          on (lineitem.l_linestatus <= lineitem.l_linestatus)
        inner join supplier
        on (supplier.s_suppkey < lineitem.l_suppkey)
      inner join customer
        inner join customer
          inner join part
          on (customer.c_custkey < customer.c_nationkey)
        on (customer.c_nationkey >= customer.c_nationkey)
      on (customer.c_nationkey <= customer.c_custkey)
    inner join lineitem
          inner join orders
          on (orders.o_orderdate <= lineitem.l_shipdate)
        inner join partsupp
            inner join supplier
            on (partsupp.ps_suppkey = supplier.s_suppkey )
          inner join lineitem
          on (supplier.s_name = lineitem.l_returnflag )
        on (orders.o_custkey <= orders.o_orderkey)
      inner join customer
          inner join part
          on (customer.c_nationkey = part.p_partkey )
        inner join part
        on (part.p_brand = customer.c_mktsegment)
      on (orders.o_orderdate < lineitem.l_shipdate)
    on (part.p_size is NULL)
where orders.o_orderpriority is not NULL;
nl: What customers have a specific market segment and are associated with certain parts that were shipped before the order date, but did not return any items?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  part.p_type
from 
  orders
        inner join nation
          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_acctbal >= supplier.s_acctbal)
        on (orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate)
      inner join part
      on (orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate)
    inner join lineitem
    on (lineitem.l_returnflag is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_shipdate is not NULL
limit 96;
nl: What are the order dates and types of parts for which the supplier's account balance is sufficient, the return flag is not null, and the shipment date is recorded?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_shipmode, 
  lineitem.l_comment, 
  lineitem.l_extendedprice, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8)), 
  lineitem.l_comment, 
  lineitem.l_partkey, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  region.r_comment, 
  lineitem.l_shipmode, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as pg_lsn) as pg_lsn)),

  region.r_regionkey, 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  region.r_comment, 
  region.r_comment
from

    inner join lineitem
    on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct < lineitem.l_returnflag)
where lineitem.l_linenumber is not NULL
limit 102;
nl: What are the shipping modes, comments, extended prices, and regions for each order, along with the maximum timestamp and minimum log sequence number?

nl: What are the part keys and available quantities of parts with comments, limited to 78?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as timestamptz) as timestamptz)), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8)), 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as "timestamp") as "timestamp")),

    cast(cast(null as text) as text)), 
  supplier.s_nationkey
from

      inner join customer
      on (supplier.s_nationkey <= supplier.s_nationkey)

    on (partsupp.ps_suppkey > supplier.s_suppkey)
where supplier.s_comment is not NULL
limit 44;
nl: What are the available quantities, supply costs, phone numbers, and other details of customers who have a comment from suppliers in a specific nation?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  lineitem.l_quantity, 
  lineitem.l_tax
from 
  lineitem
where lineitem.l_commitdate > lineitem.l_shipdate
limit 138;
nl: What are the return flags, line numbers, quantities, and taxes for all orders that were shipped after they were committed?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_name, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_name
from 
  nation
where nation.n_name > nation.n_name;
nl: What are the details of each country that has a name longer than its own description?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  orders.o_orderkey, 
  orders.o_shippriority, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  sum(
    cast(orders.o_shippriority as int4))
from 
  nation
    inner join orders
    on (orders.o_shippriority > nation.n_nationkey)
where nation.n_nationkey is NULL
limit 77;
nl: What are the nation keys, order dates, and ship priorities for nations with no key that have received more than their own priority in shipments?

sql:
select  
  min(
    cast(part.p_retailprice as "numeric")), 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  part.p_container, 
  customer.c_phone
from 
  part
    inner join customer
    on (part.p_brand < part.p_container)
where part.p_type is not NULL
limit 170;
nl: What are the minimum retail prices by nation and phone number for each brand that has a container type matching its brand, along with the corresponding phone numbers?

sql:
select  
  region.r_name, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as xid8) as xid8)), 
  region.r_regionkey
from 
  region
where region.r_name is not NULL;
nl: What are the names of regions that exist, along with their corresponding keys and a minimum value?

sql:
select  
  min(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money)), 
  nation.n_comment, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as oid) as oid)), 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval"))
from 
  orders
        inner join orders
          inner join nation
          on (nation.n_regionkey = orders.o_custkey)
        on (orders.o_shippriority <= orders.o_orderkey)
      inner join partsupp
            inner join region
            on (partsupp.ps_comment = region.r_comment )
          inner join nation
          on (partsupp.ps_supplycost <= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        inner join supplier
        on (supplier.s_name > region.r_name)
      on (nation.n_name > orders.o_orderstatus)
    inner join nation
      inner join part
      on (nation.n_regionkey = nation.n_nationkey)
    on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
where supplier.s_name < supplier.s_phone
limit 70;
nl: What is the minimum value, along with the comment for each nation, and how many intervals are there in total?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money)), 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "timestamp") as "timestamp")), 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as date) as date)), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as "timestamp") as "timestamp"))
from 
  partsupp
where partsupp.ps_availqty is NULL
limit 99;
nl: What are the part keys, maximum time intervals, available quantities, minimum monetary values, maximum timestamps, and minimum timestamps for all parts with unavailable quantities?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_comment, 
  lineitem.l_discount, 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  customer.c_acctbal, 
  customer.c_address, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  customer.c_name, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as xid8) as xid8))
from 
  nation
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_suppkey <= lineitem.l_orderkey)
      inner join customer
      on (nation.n_regionkey = customer.c_custkey )
    inner join lineitem
    on (lineitem.l_commitdate = lineitem.l_shipdate)
where lineitem.l_orderkey >= nation.n_nationkey;
nl: What are the comments, discounts, shipping instructions, outstanding balances, addresses, and market segments of customers who have placed orders with suppliers in a specific region, along with the order dates and line numbers?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_orderkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  lineitem.l_partkey
from 
  lineitem
where lineitem.l_receiptdate is NULL;
nl: What are the order keys and part keys of all line items that have no receipt date?

sql:
select  
  part.p_partkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey
from 
  region
    inner join supplier
        inner join supplier
        on (supplier.s_acctbal >= supplier.s_acctbal)
      inner join orders
            inner join part
            on (orders.o_orderstatus < orders.o_orderstatus)
          inner join part
            inner join partsupp
            on (part.p_size > part.p_size)
          on (partsupp.ps_suppkey > part.p_size)
        inner join nation
        on (orders.o_totalprice < orders.o_totalprice)
      on (supplier.s_acctbal <= supplier.s_acctbal)
    on (region.r_comment is not NULL)
where nation.n_name is not NULL
limit 78;
nl: What are the part keys and nation keys for parts with sizes larger than their own sizes, where suppliers have balances equal to or greater than their own balances?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_name, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as timestamptz) as timestamptz))
from 
  nation
where nation.n_comment is NULL
limit 129;
nl: What are the names and keys of all nations with no comments, along with a timestamp?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_custkey
from 
  orders
where orders.o_shippriority is not NULL;
nl: What customer keys are associated with shipped orders?

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(cast(null as anyarray) as anyarray))
from 
  nation
where nation.n_regionkey is NULL
limit 122;
nl: What is the maximum value from nations where the region key is null?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_suppkey, 
  lineitem.l_tax
from 
  lineitem
where lineitem.l_returnflag is NULL
limit 150;
nl: What are the supplier keys and tax rates for all line items with no return flag?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  part.p_retailprice, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey
from 
  partsupp
        inner join part
        on (part.p_brand >= part.p_mfgr)
      inner join region
      on (part.p_size < region.r_regionkey)
    inner join orders
    on (orders.o_custkey is NULL)
where orders.o_shippriority = orders.o_custkey
limit 132;
nl: What are the part keys, retail prices, and part keys of parts that have a manufacturer brand and size less than a certain region, shipped to customers with no priority?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_suppkey, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8)), 
  orders.o_orderpriority, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money))
from 
  nation
    inner join orders
        inner join part
            inner join orders
              inner join supplier
              on (supplier.s_name <= supplier.s_phone)
            on (part.p_size = supplier.s_suppkey )
          inner join partsupp
          on (supplier.s_suppkey > supplier.s_nationkey)
        on (orders.o_clerk > orders.o_orderstatus)
      inner join lineitem
      on (lineitem.l_quantity <= orders.o_totalprice)
    on (nation.n_regionkey is NULL)
where nation.n_name is not NULL
limit 101;
nl: What are the supplier keys, line numbers, average values, order priorities, and minimum prices for all suppliers that supply parts to customers with a specific region?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_suppkey
from 
  customer
    inner join partsupp
    on (customer.c_mktsegment is not NULL)
where customer.c_phone is NULL;
nl: What are the supplier keys for customers who have a market segment but no phone number?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  lineitem.l_partkey, 
  nation.n_comment
from 
  nation
    inner join lineitem
    on (lineitem.l_suppkey is NULL)
where lineitem.l_shipdate is NULL
limit 139;
nl: What are the region keys, part numbers, and comments for nations that do not supply parts?

sql:
select  
  region.r_comment
from 
  region
    inner join supplier
    on (region.r_regionkey is NULL)
where supplier.s_name is NULL
limit 60;
nl: What are the comments for regions with no corresponding suppliers, and how many of these are there?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  avg(
    cast(lineitem.l_linenumber as int4)), 
  customer.c_name, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  avg(
    cast(lineitem.l_partkey as int4)), 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  lineitem.l_discount, 
  lineitem.l_discount, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  region.r_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  nation.n_comment
from 
  lineitem
        inner join nation
        on (lineitem.l_partkey <= nation.n_nationkey)
      inner join partsupp
              inner join supplier
              on (supplier.s_name < supplier.s_phone)
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_discount > lineitem.l_discount)
          inner join region
          on (lineitem.l_returnflag < lineitem.l_shipmode)
        inner join lineitem
          inner join part
          on (lineitem.l_shipdate > lineitem.l_commitdate)
        on (lineitem.l_partkey > partsupp.ps_partkey)
      on (supplier.s_suppkey > lineitem.l_orderkey)
    inner join customer
            inner join lineitem
            on (customer.c_custkey < lineitem.l_suppkey)
          inner join lineitem
            inner join region
            on (lineitem.l_discount = lineitem.l_discount)
          on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct > lineitem.l_shipmode)
        inner join nation
        on (lineitem.l_extendedprice > lineitem.l_tax)
      inner join customer
      on (lineitem.l_orderkey < customer.c_custkey)
    on (region.r_comment is NULL)
where supplier.s_acctbal is not NULL;
nl: What are the shipping instructions, average linenumber, names of customers, and other details for each order that has a non-zero account balance with its supplier?

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as text) as text)), 
  max(
    cast(supplier.s_nationkey as int4)), 
  avg(
    cast(supplier.s_acctbal as "numeric")), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  supplier.s_name, 
  supplier.s_name
from 
  supplier
where supplier.s_acctbal >= supplier.s_acctbal
limit 94;
nl: What is the maximum value of null, along with the account balance, comment, phone number, address, and name for each supplier that has an account balance greater than or equal to their own account balance?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  max(
    cast(part.p_container as bpchar)), 
  sum(
    cast(lineitem.l_tax as "numeric")), 
  sum(
    cast(lineitem.l_tax as "numeric"))
from 
  supplier
        inner join part
          inner join nation
              inner join nation
              on (nation.n_regionkey = nation.n_nationkey)
            inner join nation
            on (nation.n_name < nation.n_name)
          on (nation.n_nationkey = nation.n_regionkey)
        on (supplier.s_suppkey = nation.n_nationkey )
      inner join customer
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_quantity <= lineitem.l_quantity)
      on (lineitem.l_receiptdate < lineitem.l_receiptdate)
    inner join orders
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_quantity <= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
      inner join partsupp
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_quantity <= lineitem.l_quantity)
        inner join supplier
          inner join partsupp
            inner join nation
              inner join part
              on (part.p_retailprice >= part.p_retailprice)
            on (nation.n_name = part.p_container)
          on (supplier.s_suppkey = partsupp.ps_partkey )
        on (part.p_retailprice > lineitem.l_quantity)
      on (lineitem.l_commitdate < lineitem.l_receiptdate)
    on (supplier.s_suppkey < partsupp.ps_partkey)
where lineitem.l_receiptdate is not NULL
limit 180;
nl: What are the commit dates, part keys, maximum container sizes, total taxes, and total tax amounts for all orders that have a receipt date later than their commit date?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_address, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  customer.c_comment
from 
  customer
    inner join supplier
    on (customer.c_acctbal > customer.c_acctbal)
where supplier.s_suppkey > customer.c_custkey;
nl: What are the addresses and account balances of suppliers who have more significant accounts than their customers, along with any comments left by those customers?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as timestamptz) as timestamptz))
from 
  orders
    inner join region
      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
    on (region.r_name is NULL)
where orders.o_orderpriority is not NULL
limit 141;
nl: What is the total price of each order, and what is the latest timestamp?

sql:
select

  part.p_mfgr,

  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8))
from 
  partsupp
        inner join supplier
            inner join part
            on (part.p_retailprice < supplier.s_acctbal)
          inner join customer

                inner join part
                on (part.p_mfgr > part.p_brand)
              inner join orders
              on (customer.c_acctbal < orders.o_totalprice)
            on (orders.o_orderstatus = customer.c_mktsegment)

      inner join region

    inner join partsupp
      inner join partsupp
        inner join partsupp
            inner join part
            on (partsupp.ps_availqty > partsupp.ps_suppkey)
          inner join region
          on (region.r_regionkey = partsupp.ps_availqty)
        on (partsupp.ps_partkey <= region.r_regionkey)

select

from 
  part
      inner join supplier
            inner join supplier
              inner join part
              on (part.p_partkey < supplier.s_nationkey)
            on (supplier.s_acctbal <= supplier.s_acctbal)
          inner join supplier
          on (part.p_retailprice = part.p_retailprice)
        inner join region
            inner join nation
            on (region.r_name < region.r_name)
          inner join part
            inner join region
              inner join region
              on (region.r_regionkey = region.r_regionkey )
            on (part.p_container = region.r_name )
          on (part.p_mfgr = part.p_mfgr)
        on (supplier.s_nationkey = region.r_regionkey )
      on (part.p_partkey >= nation.n_nationkey)
    inner join region
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
        inner join supplier
            inner join supplier
            on (supplier.s_name < supplier.s_phone)
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct > supplier.s_phone)
        on (lineitem.l_suppkey > lineitem.l_orderkey)
      inner join supplier
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_extendedprice < supplier.s_acctbal)
      on (region.r_regionkey = supplier.s_suppkey )
    on (nation.n_regionkey = region.r_regionkey )

        on (partsupp.ps_suppkey >= lineitem.l_orderkey)
      on (nation.n_name = lineitem.l_returnflag )
    inner join nation
    on (nation.n_name is not NULL)
where nation.n_nationkey is not NULL;
nl: What are the minimum values, along with the nation key, supplier key, nation name, and part key, for all nations that have a specific return flag?

sql:
select distinct 
  part.p_brand, 
  part.p_container
from 
  nation
      inner join part
      on (nation.n_name = part.p_mfgr )
    inner join customer
    on (customer.c_name is not NULL)
where part.p_mfgr is NULL;
nl: What are the unique brands and containers of parts manufactured by nations that do not produce any parts, and which customers have purchased these parts?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as text) as text)), 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money)), 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey
from

where partsupp.ps_supplycost is NULL
limit 81;
nl: What are the supply costs and supplier keys for all suppliers with no supply cost?

sql:
select

from 
  partsupp
where partsupp.ps_availqty is not NULL
limit 100;
nl: What part numbers are available in stock?

sql:
select  
  part.p_name, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  max(
    cast(lineitem.l_quantity as "numeric")), 
  max(
    cast(part.p_retailprice as "numeric")), 
  region.r_name, 
  max(
    cast(lineitem.l_shipdate as date)), 
  part.p_container, 
  region.r_comment, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as timestamptz) as timestamptz)), 
  supplier.s_address, 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  max(
    cast(part.p_container as bpchar)), 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  supplier.s_acctbal
from 
  lineitem
    inner join part
        inner join nation
          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_acctbal < supplier.s_acctbal)
        on (nation.n_nationkey = supplier.s_suppkey)
      inner join partsupp
          inner join region
          on (region.r_name <= region.r_name)
        inner join region
            inner join part
            on (part.p_retailprice = part.p_retailprice)
          inner join part
          on (region.r_regionkey < part.p_partkey)
        on (partsupp.ps_supplycost >= part.p_retailprice)
      on (supplier.s_phone = part.p_container)
    on (lineitem.l_shipdate = lineitem.l_commitdate)
where lineitem.l_commitdate > lineitem.l_commitdate;
nl: What are the names of parts, their supply costs, maximum quantities ordered, retail prices, regions, and latest shipment dates? Give me the container types, region comments, earliest possible dates, supplier addresses, order statuses, and total quantities for each part.

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as anyenum) as anyenum)), 
  lineitem.l_suppkey
from 
  supplier
    inner join customer
      inner join lineitem
        inner join orders
            inner join lineitem
            on (orders.o_custkey = lineitem.l_orderkey )
          inner join orders
            inner join lineitem
                inner join customer
                on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_commitdate)
              inner join lineitem
              on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_shipdate)
            on (lineitem.l_linenumber >= lineitem.l_partkey)
          on (lineitem.l_linestatus > customer.c_mktsegment)
        on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct > lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
      on (orders.o_orderdate > lineitem.l_receiptdate)
    on (lineitem.l_suppkey is not NULL)
where customer.c_phone is NULL;
nl: What suppliers have no phone number and what are their account balances, along with the maximum value?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_comment
from 
  part
    inner join supplier
    on (part.p_type = supplier.s_address )
where supplier.s_name < part.p_brand
limit 150;
nl: What are the comments from suppliers that provide parts with brands that come after their names in alphabetical order, and give me up to 150 results?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_linestatus,

  lineitem.l_partkey

where lineitem.l_shipdate > lineitem.l_receiptdate
limit 130;
nl: What are the l_linestatus, maximum value, discount, and part numbers for orders that were shipped after they were received?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_orderstatus, 
  orders.o_custkey, 
  orders.o_orderdate,

where orders.o_clerk > orders.o_orderstatus
limit 38;
nl: What are the order status, customer key, order date, and priority of all orders where the clerk's rating exceeds the order's status, along with any additional information?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey
from

where partsupp.ps_supplycost <= partsupp.ps_supplycost;
nl: What are the part keys and their own supply costs for all suppliers with a supply cost that is equal to or less than itself?

sql:
select  
  region.r_comment,

from

    inner join nation
      inner join part

    on (part.p_partkey is not NULL)

limit 86;
nl: What are the names and comments of regions where parts with non-null retail prices exist?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_custkey, 
  customer.c_comment, 
  customer.c_nationkey,

from

limit 92;
nl: What are the details of customers with a valid address, including their key, comment, and nation key, along with any additional information?

sql:
select

from 
  part
where part.p_brand is not NULL
limit 79;
nl: What are the retail prices of parts from non-null brands?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  lineitem.l_extendedprice, 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate
from 
  lineitem
where lineitem.l_linenumber is not NULL;
nl: What are the shipping instructions, total value, prices, and receipt dates for all non-null line items?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  lineitem.l_orderkey, 
  lineitem.l_discount, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as timestamptz) as timestamptz)), 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  supplier.s_comment
from 
  lineitem
      inner join partsupp
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_returnflag >= lineitem.l_linestatus)
      on (lineitem.l_linestatus > lineitem.l_returnflag)
    inner join part
          inner join lineitem
            inner join supplier
            on (lineitem.l_suppkey = supplier.s_suppkey )
          on (part.p_mfgr = lineitem.l_returnflag )
        inner join lineitem
        on (supplier.s_phone <= supplier.s_name)
      inner join lineitem
        inner join partsupp
          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_name < supplier.s_name)
        on (lineitem.l_suppkey = partsupp.ps_partkey )
      on (lineitem.l_tax <= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
    on (supplier.s_comment is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_comment is NULL
limit 61;
nl: What are the part numbers, return flags, comments, nation keys, order keys, discounts, and maximum timestamps for all suppliers who have a comment, along with their corresponding parts that have no comments?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_address, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey,

    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2))
from 
  customer
    inner join partsupp
    on (customer.c_acctbal < customer.c_acctbal)
where customer.c_acctbal is not NULL
limit 138;

sql:
select  
  region.r_comment,

  region.r_comment
from

where region.r_name is not NULL;

      inner join partsupp

      on (lineitem.l_tax > lineitem.l_extendedprice)
    inner join customer
    on (lineitem.l_returnflag > region.r_name)
where customer.c_mktsegment < region.r_name
limit 163;

sql:

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)),

where nation.n_name is NULL;

    inner join part
    on (nation.n_regionkey is not NULL)
where part.p_name is not NULL
limit 35;

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_comment, 
  part.p_size, 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  part.p_container, 
  part.p_size, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  part.p_size, 
  part.p_partkey, 
  lineitem.l_tax, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  part.p_comment, 
  part.p_brand
from 
  lineitem
    inner join partsupp
        inner join supplier
          inner join nation
            inner join part
            on (nation.n_regionkey >= part.p_size)
          on (part.p_retailprice <= supplier.s_acctbal)
        on (partsupp.ps_supplycost = part.p_retailprice )
      inner join part
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_shipdate = lineitem.l_shipdate)
      on (partsupp.ps_availqty = part.p_size)
    on (partsupp.ps_availqty >= lineitem.l_suppkey)
where part.p_partkey is NULL;
nl: What are the supplier comments, part sizes, phone numbers, container types, and maximum values for parts with no key, along with their shipping instructions, taxes, availability quantities, receipt dates, and brand information?

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(cast(null as timestamptz) as timestamptz)), 
  region.r_comment, 
  region.r_name
from 
  region
where region.r_regionkey is NULL
limit 162;

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  customer.c_nationkey
from 
  lineitem
      inner join customer
        inner join nation
        on (nation.n_regionkey >= nation.n_regionkey)
      on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
    inner join customer
    on (customer.c_nationkey < lineitem.l_linenumber)
where lineitem.l_commitdate = lineitem.l_receiptdate
limit 114;

sql:
select  
  part.p_mfgr
from 
  part
where part.p_partkey >= part.p_partkey
limit 123;
nl: What are the manufacturers of parts with a key greater than or equal to themselves, and give me 123 results?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_nationkey
from 
  nation
where nation.n_nationkey is NULL;
nl: What are the comments and nation keys for nations with no key?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_tax
from 
  orders
    inner join supplier
      inner join lineitem
        inner join orders
        on (orders.o_orderdate <= orders.o_orderdate)
      on (lineitem.l_commitdate = lineitem.l_commitdate)
    on (supplier.s_address is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_receiptdate = lineitem.l_commitdate;
nl: What are the tax amounts for all orders that have been received and committed at the same time, given that the supplier's address is available?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost
from 
  partsupp
where partsupp.ps_supplycost is NULL
limit 100;
nl: What are the part-supplier combinations with no supply cost information, along with their available quantity and supplier key?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_suppkey, 
  customer.c_name, 
  supplier.s_phone
from 
  supplier
      inner join customer
          inner join customer
          on (customer.c_phone <= customer.c_mktsegment)
        inner join region
          inner join region
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
          on (region.r_regionkey <= region.r_regionkey)
        on (customer.c_name = lineitem.l_comment )
      on (lineitem.l_returnflag <= customer.c_phone)
    inner join customer
      inner join part
      on (customer.c_acctbal = customer.c_acctbal)
    on (customer.c_custkey is NULL)
where customer.c_acctbal is not NULL
limit 112;
nl: What are the supplier keys, customer names, and phone numbers of customers who have a market segment and an account balance, with receipts that happened after shipments, and whose comments match their names?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_comment
from 
  customer
        inner join customer
        on (customer.c_acctbal <= customer.c_acctbal)
      inner join part
          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_nationkey >= part.p_partkey)
        inner join partsupp
        on (supplier.s_suppkey = partsupp.ps_partkey )
      on (customer.c_phone = part.p_mfgr )
    inner join partsupp
    on (supplier.s_name is NULL)
where customer.c_custkey is NULL
limit 137;
nl: What are the comments left by customers who have not paid their bills and whose phone number matches a manufacturer's name?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_comment
from 
  partsupp
where partsupp.ps_supplycost >= partsupp.ps_supplycost
limit 121;
nl: What are the comments and supply costs for all suppliers that have a supply cost equal to or greater than their own supply cost?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_discount, 
  part.p_brand, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  region.r_name
from 
  part
    inner join lineitem
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_commitdate >= lineitem.l_commitdate)
      inner join region
      on (lineitem.l_discount < lineitem.l_quantity)
    on (lineitem.l_linenumber is NULL)
where part.p_mfgr >= lineitem.l_shipmode
limit 119;
nl: What are the discount rates, brands of parts, regions, and names for orders that have not been shipped yet?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_name, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_name, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  count(
    cast(nation.n_name as bpchar)), 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey
from 
  nation
where nation.n_nationkey is not NULL
limit 107;
nl: What are the names and comments of all nations that exist, along with how many times each nation appears in the data?

sql:
select  
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  orders.o_shippriority, 
  orders.o_custkey, 
  orders.o_orderstatus, 
  orders.o_clerk, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money)), 
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  orders.o_custkey
from 
  orders
where orders.o_orderstatus >= orders.o_orderpriority
limit 70;
nl: What is the total count of orders with a status equal to or higher than their priority, along with other details such as ship priority, customer key, order status, clerk, maximum total price, and order date?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_clerk, 
  orders.o_clerk, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  customer.c_address
from 
  orders
        inner join supplier
          inner join partsupp
          on (partsupp.ps_availqty > supplier.s_suppkey)
        on (supplier.s_phone > orders.o_clerk)
      inner join region
      on (supplier.s_acctbal > orders.o_totalprice)
    inner join customer
    on (partsupp.ps_supplycost is not NULL)
where orders.o_custkey is not NULL
limit 159;
nl: What are the names of the sales clerks, their average availability, and the addresses of customers who have placed large orders with suppliers from a specific region?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  count(
    cast(orders.o_orderdate as date)), 
  lineitem.l_quantity, 
  orders.o_clerk, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money)), 
  customer.c_comment, 
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  lineitem.l_quantity, 
  orders.o_clerk, 
  lineitem.l_tax, 
  orders.o_orderstatus, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  orders.o_orderdate
from 
  supplier
    inner join orders
        inner join lineitem
          inner join lineitem
              inner join partsupp
                inner join supplier
                on (partsupp.ps_comment = supplier.s_address )
              on (lineitem.l_orderkey < lineitem.l_orderkey)
            inner join customer
              inner join orders
                inner join lineitem
                on (orders.o_orderkey > orders.o_shippriority)
              on (lineitem.l_shipdate <= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
            on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct >= customer.c_mktsegment)
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_commitdate)
        on (orders.o_totalprice < lineitem.l_discount)
      inner join supplier
        inner join customer
          inner join part
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_acctbal = customer.c_acctbal)
          on (customer.c_comment = customer.c_name )
        on (part.p_retailprice > customer.c_acctbal)
      on (lineitem.l_shipdate < orders.o_orderdate)
    on (part.p_name is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_linenumber is not NULL;
nl: What are the market segments, account balances, return flags, and order counts for each customer, along with their comments, phone numbers, and order details?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_shipmode, 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  lineitem.l_commitdate
from 
  lineitem
where lineitem.l_shipmode > lineitem.l_linestatus;
nl: What modes of shipping and instructions were used for orders that have not yet been committed?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  sum(
    cast(lineitem.l_linenumber as int4)), 
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  customer.c_address, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as anyarray) as anyarray)), 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  lineitem.l_orderkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as tid) as tid)), 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  lineitem.l_suppkey, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8)), 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  customer.c_acctbal, 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  nation.n_name, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  avg(
    cast(customer.c_nationkey as int4))
from 
  lineitem
      inner join supplier
      on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct > supplier.s_name)
    inner join lineitem
      inner join customer
          inner join region
          on (customer.c_custkey >= customer.c_nationkey)
        inner join nation
        on (nation.n_name < customer.c_phone)
      on (lineitem.l_commitdate > lineitem.l_commitdate)
    on (supplier.s_address = nation.n_comment )
where lineitem.l_suppkey >= lineitem.l_partkey
limit 42;
nl: What are the region keys, total order numbers, supplier keys, customer addresses, and average nation keys for each nation where the supplier's name is greater than the shipping instruction?

sql:
select  
  region.r_comment, 
  region.r_regionkey
from 
  region
where region.r_regionkey is not NULL
limit 85;
nl: What are the comments and regions for which there is a non-null key?

sql:
select  
  part.p_name, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  region.r_name, 
  orders.o_custkey, 
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  part.p_comment
from 
  part
    inner join orders
      inner join region
          inner join partsupp
            inner join part
            on (partsupp.ps_supplycost = partsupp.ps_supplycost)
          on (partsupp.ps_supplycost < part.p_retailprice)
        inner join part
        on (region.r_comment = part.p_name )
      on (part.p_mfgr > part.p_container)
    on (orders.o_comment is NULL)
where orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate;
nl: What are the names of parts, their available quantities, regions, customer keys, total prices, supply costs, and comments for customers who have ordered products at a lower price than their retail price?

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "timestamp") as "timestamp")), 
  customer.c_name, 
  customer.c_address, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as oid) as oid))
from 
  customer
where customer.c_custkey is NULL;
nl: What are the maximum timestamp, customer name, address, nation key, and cust key for customers with no cust key?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  part.p_mfgr, 
  lineitem.l_discount, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_name, 
  part.p_type, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as anyenum) as anyenum))
from 
  nation
          inner join supplier
            inner join part
                inner join nation
                on (part.p_brand < part.p_container)
              inner join partsupp
                inner join lineitem
                on (lineitem.l_shipmode = lineitem.l_shipmode)
              on (lineitem.l_shipdate < lineitem.l_shipdate)
            on (lineitem.l_orderkey <= lineitem.l_linenumber)
          on (lineitem.l_tax = lineitem.l_extendedprice)
        inner join lineitem
          inner join part
          on (lineitem.l_quantity >= part.p_retailprice)
        on (lineitem.l_receiptdate <= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
      inner join supplier
      on (part.p_mfgr = part.p_mfgr)
    inner join region
    on (lineitem.l_linenumber is not NULL)
where part.p_partkey = lineitem.l_partkey;
nl: What are the details of each part, including manufacturer, discount, supply cost, and type, for all parts that have been supplied to a specific nation?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_nationkey
from 
  nation
where nation.n_name <= nation.n_name;
nl: What are the nation keys for nations with names that come before themselves?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_discount, 
  lineitem.l_suppkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "time") as "time")), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as "time") as "time")), 
  lineitem.l_linestatus,

from 
  lineitem
where lineitem.l_extendedprice >= lineitem.l_quantity
limit 158;
nl: What are the discount, supplier key, and status of each line item that has a price equal to or greater than its quantity?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  orders.o_custkey, 
  orders.o_orderkey, 
  part.p_type, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  part.p_comment, 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  part.p_container, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_name, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_name, 
  orders.o_clerk, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as pg_lsn) as pg_lsn)), 
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as anyenum) as anyenum))
from 
  part
    inner join lineitem
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_shipdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
        inner join supplier
          inner join orders
            inner join supplier
            on (supplier.s_suppkey = supplier.s_nationkey)
          on (orders.o_orderkey > orders.o_custkey)
        on (orders.o_orderdate <= lineitem.l_shipdate)
      inner join nation
      on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct <= nation.n_name)
    on (lineitem.l_quantity is NULL)
where supplier.s_suppkey = part.p_size
limit 57;
nl: What are the details of all orders that were shipped to a specific nation, including information about the customer, order date, and shipping instructions?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_mktsegment,

    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)),

sql:
select distinct 
  region.r_comment, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as tid) as tid)), 
  part.p_name, 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  part.p_type
from 
  customer
      inner join part
        inner join lineitem
          inner join part
          on (lineitem.l_shipdate <= lineitem.l_commitdate)
        on (lineitem.l_suppkey = part.p_size)
      on (lineitem.l_quantity <= lineitem.l_tax)
    inner join lineitem
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_custkey >= customer.c_custkey)
          inner join customer
          on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct = lineitem.l_linestatus)
        inner join part
          inner join region
          on (part.p_brand >= region.r_name)
        on (part.p_container >= part.p_container)
      inner join nation
        inner join customer
        on (nation.n_regionkey = customer.c_custkey )
      on (lineitem.l_shipmode >= customer.c_mktsegment)
    on (part.p_container < customer.c_mktsegment)
where customer.c_address is NULL;
nl: What are the distinct comments from each region, along with the maximum value, part names, order statuses, commit dates, and types of parts that have not been shipped yet?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_comment, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  customer.c_name, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  customer.c_comment, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  region.r_regionkey
from 
  customer
    inner join customer
      inner join supplier
          inner join region
          on (region.r_name > supplier.s_phone)
        inner join part
        on (supplier.s_nationkey = supplier.s_suppkey)
      on (customer.c_acctbal < customer.c_acctbal)
    on (supplier.s_suppkey is not NULL)
where part.p_partkey <= customer.c_custkey
limit 110;
nl: What are the comments, customer information, and region details of customers who have purchased parts with a specific supplier, along with the supplier's account balance?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_comment, 
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  region.r_name, 
  nation.n_name, 
  region.r_comment, 
  orders.o_shippriority, 
  orders.o_shippriority, 
  region.r_name
from 
  orders
      inner join orders
          inner join nation
          on (orders.o_orderkey = nation.n_nationkey )
        inner join customer
        on (orders.o_clerk = customer.c_phone )
      on (customer.c_phone > orders.o_orderstatus)
    inner join supplier
      inner join partsupp
          inner join orders
              inner join region
              on (region.r_name >= orders.o_orderpriority)
            inner join supplier
              inner join part
              on (supplier.s_acctbal > supplier.s_acctbal)
            on (region.r_comment = part.p_name )
          on (part.p_retailprice >= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        inner join part
        on (supplier.s_name > part.p_brand)
      on (partsupp.ps_availqty <= part.p_partkey)
    on (supplier.s_comment is NULL)
where orders.o_orderpriority is not NULL;
nl: What are the comments, order dates, region names, nation names, and ship priorities for all orders that have a specific priority, with additional information about the supplier, part, and availability?

sql:
select  
  region.r_name, 
  part.p_brand, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  part.p_container, 
  part.p_size
from 
  part
        inner join supplier
        on (part.p_size <= supplier.s_nationkey)
      inner join part
            inner join part
            on (part.p_comment = part.p_name )
          inner join region
          on (part.p_comment = region.r_comment )
        inner join nation
        on (nation.n_nationkey >= nation.n_nationkey)
      on (part.p_size < region.r_regionkey)
    inner join partsupp
      inner join supplier
      on (supplier.s_acctbal >= supplier.s_acctbal)
    on (part.p_size < supplier.s_suppkey)
where part.p_retailprice >= partsupp.ps_supplycost;
nl: What are the regions, brands, part keys, nation keys, and comments for suppliers that provide parts with a retail price greater than or equal to their supply cost?

    cast(cast(null as oid) as oid))
from

          inner join nation
          on (nation.n_nationkey < nation.n_nationkey)
        inner join region
          inner join lineitem
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_linenumber > lineitem.l_orderkey)
          on (lineitem.l_quantity = lineitem.l_quantity)
        on (nation.n_name = region.r_name )
      inner join part
      on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct <= lineitem.l_linestatus)
    inner join partsupp
      inner join region
      on (region.r_name >= region.r_name)
    on (region.r_comment is not NULL)

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(lineitem.l_commitdate as date)), 
  region.r_comment, 
  part.p_brand, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  region.r_name
from 
  orders
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_linestatus <= lineitem.l_returnflag)
          inner join region
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_mktsegment < region.r_name)
          on (lineitem.l_receiptdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
        inner join lineitem
          inner join region
          on (lineitem.l_quantity > lineitem.l_tax)
        on (customer.c_phone >= lineitem.l_linestatus)
      inner join part
        inner join lineitem
        on (part.p_type = lineitem.l_comment )
      on (part.p_partkey > orders.o_shippriority)
    inner join orders
      inner join nation
      on (orders.o_orderpriority = nation.n_name )
    on (lineitem.l_linestatus = orders.o_orderstatus )
where orders.o_orderstatus is not NULL
limit 137;

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_phone, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  region.r_name, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money)), 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as xid8) as xid8)), 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as date) as date)), 
  supplier.s_name, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as date) as date)), 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  nation.n_name, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  region.r_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty
from 
  nation
        inner join nation
          inner join customer
          on (customer.c_nationkey > customer.c_nationkey)
        on (nation.n_name >= nation.n_name)
      inner join region
        inner join nation
          inner join partsupp
            inner join partsupp
            on (partsupp.ps_supplycost > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
          on (partsupp.ps_supplycost = partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        on (partsupp.ps_partkey <= partsupp.ps_partkey)
      on (nation.n_regionkey <= nation.n_regionkey)
    inner join region
      inner join supplier
            inner join supplier
            on (supplier.s_suppkey <= supplier.s_nationkey)
          inner join partsupp
          on (supplier.s_acctbal <= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        inner join region
            inner join partsupp
            on (partsupp.ps_availqty = partsupp.ps_partkey)
          inner join nation
          on (nation.n_nationkey = nation.n_regionkey)
        on (region.r_regionkey >= supplier.s_suppkey)
      on (supplier.s_name = nation.n_name)
    on (region.r_name is not NULL)
where supplier.s_acctbal >= supplier.s_acctbal;

        on (nation.n_regionkey < lineitem.l_orderkey)
      on (lineitem.l_discount = lineitem.l_quantity )

sql:
select

  sum(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)),

  supplier.s_phone
from

          inner join orders
            inner join region
                inner join part
                on (region.r_name = part.p_mfgr )
              inner join nation
                inner join lineitem
                on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
              on (lineitem.l_shipmode <= nation.n_name)
            on (part.p_retailprice < lineitem.l_discount)
          on (nation.n_name = lineitem.l_returnflag )
        inner join supplier
        on (part.p_retailprice >= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
      inner join region
      on (lineitem.l_discount <= orders.o_totalprice)
    on (region.r_comment is not NULL)
where supplier.s_address is NULL

sql:
select  
  customer.c_address
from 
  orders
        inner join nation
        on (orders.o_totalprice < orders.o_totalprice)
      inner join orders
        inner join region
          inner join customer
          on (customer.c_acctbal <= customer.c_acctbal)
        on (orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate)
      on (orders.o_orderkey >= orders.o_orderkey)
    inner join partsupp
            inner join region
            on (region.r_regionkey = partsupp.ps_partkey)
          inner join region
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_totalprice < orders.o_totalprice)
          on (region.r_name >= orders.o_clerk)
        inner join supplier
        on (orders.o_shippriority = orders.o_orderkey)
      inner join region
          inner join customer
          on (customer.c_acctbal >= customer.c_acctbal)
        inner join orders
            inner join region
              inner join nation
              on (region.r_name = nation.n_name)
            on (orders.o_totalprice = orders.o_totalprice)
          inner join part
          on (part.p_retailprice < orders.o_totalprice)
        on (part.p_retailprice > customer.c_acctbal)
      on (partsupp.ps_supplycost > orders.o_totalprice)
    on (orders.o_shippriority < partsupp.ps_suppkey)
where nation.n_comment is NULL;

        on (orders.o_orderdate > orders.o_orderdate)
      on (orders.o_orderstatus >= part.p_container)
    inner join supplier
      inner join supplier
      on (supplier.s_phone = supplier.s_name)
    on (orders.o_clerk is not NULL)
where supplier.s_nationkey is NULL
limit 148;

  orders.o_orderstatus, 
  customer.c_comment, 
  supplier.s_suppkey
from 
  supplier
          inner join partsupp
            inner join supplier
            on (partsupp.ps_supplycost < supplier.s_acctbal)
          on (supplier.s_comment = supplier.s_address )
        inner join orders
          inner join orders
            inner join supplier
            on (orders.o_totalprice <= orders.o_totalprice)
          on (orders.o_orderpriority >= supplier.s_phone)
        on (orders.o_custkey < partsupp.ps_partkey)
      inner join customer
          inner join partsupp
          on (customer.c_acctbal >= customer.c_acctbal)
        inner join supplier
        on (customer.c_mktsegment = supplier.s_name )
      on (supplier.s_nationkey > partsupp.ps_suppkey)
    inner join partsupp
    on (supplier.s_comment is not NULL)
where partsupp.ps_supplycost is not NULL

            inner join lineitem

            on (orders.o_comment = lineitem.l_comment )
          inner join supplier
          on (lineitem.l_shipdate = lineitem.l_receiptdate)
        on (lineitem.l_shipdate <= lineitem.l_shipdate)
      on (part.p_retailprice >= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
    on (supplier.s_suppkey = part.p_size)
where part.p_brand is not NULL;

sql:
select  
  part.p_mfgr,

  part.p_mfgr, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as xid8) as xid8)), 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  part.p_mfgr, 
  part.p_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  nation.n_comment
from 
  orders
    inner join orders
          inner join nation
          on (orders.o_totalprice < orders.o_totalprice)
        inner join lineitem
          inner join part
                inner join supplier
                on (part.p_container < supplier.s_phone)
              inner join part
              on (part.p_mfgr = part.p_mfgr)
            inner join partsupp
              inner join part
              on (partsupp.ps_comment = part.p_name )
            on (part.p_retailprice < supplier.s_acctbal)
          on (lineitem.l_partkey <= supplier.s_nationkey)
        on (part.p_size = part.p_partkey)
      inner join orders
      on (supplier.s_acctbal > lineitem.l_extendedprice)
    on (orders.o_orderstatus = lineitem.l_returnflag )
where part.p_size is not NULL
limit 99;

sql:
select  
  nation.n_name, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  customer.c_name, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  lineitem.l_suppkey, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "timestamp") as "timestamp")), 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  supplier.s_name, 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "timestamp") as "timestamp")), 
  supplier.s_suppkey
from 
  nation
      inner join supplier
      on (supplier.s_acctbal >= supplier.s_acctbal)
    inner join lineitem
      inner join supplier
        inner join customer
        on (supplier.s_acctbal <= supplier.s_acctbal)
      on (lineitem.l_tax < customer.c_acctbal)
    on (supplier.s_comment = supplier.s_address )
where lineitem.l_shipinstruct < supplier.s_name;
nl: What are the names of nations, suppliers, and customers that have specific characteristics, along with their addresses, phone numbers, market segments, and comments?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_clerk, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  customer.c_name, 
  customer.c_address, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  region.r_name
from 
  partsupp
    inner join nation
      inner join supplier
          inner join customer
          on (customer.c_custkey <= supplier.s_suppkey)
        inner join region
              inner join customer
                inner join lineitem
                  inner join orders
                  on (orders.o_orderpriority <= orders.o_orderpriority)
                on (customer.c_acctbal = orders.o_totalprice )
              on (customer.c_acctbal < lineitem.l_tax)
            inner join customer
            on (orders.o_custkey > customer.c_nationkey)
          inner join customer
              inner join lineitem
              on (lineitem.l_returnflag > lineitem.l_shipmode)
            inner join region
            on (lineitem.l_tax > lineitem.l_tax)
          on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_receiptdate)
        on (lineitem.l_linestatus >= lineitem.l_returnflag)
      on (orders.o_totalprice >= customer.c_acctbal)
    on (supplier.s_acctbal is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_shipinstruct is NULL
limit 46;

select

    cast(cast(null as xid8) as xid8)),

from

      inner join nation
          inner join part

          on (lineitem.l_quantity >= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
        inner join orders
        on (lineitem.l_linestatus >= part.p_brand)
      on (lineitem.l_tax = orders.o_totalprice)
    inner join region
      inner join customer
        inner join part
        on (customer.c_nationkey < customer.c_custkey)
      on (customer.c_acctbal < part.p_retailprice)
    on (part.p_retailprice is NULL)
where customer.c_comment is NULL

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_name, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey
from 
  lineitem
      inner join supplier
      on (lineitem.l_suppkey <= lineitem.l_suppkey)
    inner join part
            inner join orders
            on (part.p_retailprice >= orders.o_totalprice)
          inner join lineitem
              inner join partsupp
              on (lineitem.l_extendedprice = partsupp.ps_supplycost )
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_orderpriority >= lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
          on (lineitem.l_discount > lineitem.l_quantity)
        inner join supplier
              inner join partsupp
              on (supplier.s_acctbal = partsupp.ps_supplycost)
            inner join region
              inner join customer
              on (region.r_name = customer.c_phone )
            on (customer.c_phone = customer.c_mktsegment)
          inner join supplier
          on (customer.c_comment = supplier.s_address )
        on (orders.o_clerk > region.r_name)
      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_orderdate <= lineitem.l_commitdate)
    on (supplier.s_address is not NULL)
where orders.o_totalprice < supplier.s_acctbal
limit 174;

select

      inner join orders
        inner join orders
          inner join nation
          on (nation.n_nationkey > orders.o_orderkey)
        on (orders.o_shippriority > orders.o_orderkey)
      on (customer.c_mktsegment >= orders.o_orderpriority)
    inner join supplier
          inner join region
          on (supplier.s_nationkey = region.r_regionkey )
        inner join region
        on (supplier.s_acctbal = supplier.s_acctbal)

          inner join supplier

            inner join partsupp
            on (supplier.s_acctbal < supplier.s_acctbal)
          on (lineitem.l_orderkey = supplier.s_suppkey )
        on (partsupp.ps_suppkey > nation.n_nationkey)

        inner join lineitem
            inner join partsupp
            on (lineitem.l_extendedprice = partsupp.ps_supplycost )
          inner join lineitem
            inner join nation
              inner join lineitem
              on (lineitem.l_linestatus <= lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
            on (lineitem.l_partkey <= lineitem.l_orderkey)
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate < lineitem.l_commitdate)
        on (orders.o_orderdate = lineitem.l_shipdate)
      on (orders.o_clerk < lineitem.l_shipmode)

sql:
select  
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as "time") as "time")), 
  part.p_type, 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  min(
    cast(part.p_partkey as int4)), 
  part.p_mfgr, 
  region.r_name, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  part.p_retailprice, 
  region.r_name, 
  min(
    cast(supplier.s_acctbal as "numeric")), 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  customer.c_name, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  orders.o_orderpriority
from 
  region
        inner join customer
        on (region.r_comment = customer.c_name )
      inner join orders
        inner join part
          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_acctbal = supplier.s_acctbal)
        on (orders.o_totalprice < supplier.s_acctbal)
      on (supplier.s_phone > region.r_name)
    inner join part
          inner join region
            inner join part
            on (part.p_size >= part.p_size)
          on (part.p_size = part.p_partkey)
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_discount > lineitem.l_extendedprice)
      inner join part
              inner join nation
              on (part.p_mfgr = part.p_container)
            inner join supplier
                inner join region
                on (supplier.s_acctbal <= supplier.s_acctbal)
              inner join customer
              on (region.r_name = customer.c_phone )
            on (part.p_brand > customer.c_phone)
          inner join customer
            inner join orders
              inner join orders
              on (orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate)
            on (customer.c_phone = orders.o_orderstatus)
          on (supplier.s_acctbal >= orders.o_totalprice)
        inner join customer
        on (customer.c_nationkey >= customer.c_custkey)
      on (orders.o_totalprice < lineitem.l_quantity)
    on (part.p_partkey is not NULL)
where region.r_regionkey > orders.o_orderkey;

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_extendedprice, 
  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  customer.c_comment, 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  nation.n_name, 
  sum(
    cast(lineitem.l_extendedprice as "numeric")), 
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  orders.o_shippriority, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  lineitem.l_shipmode
from 
  customer
      inner join orders
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_clerk <= orders.o_orderpriority)
          inner join lineitem
          on (orders.o_custkey = lineitem.l_orderkey )
        inner join customer
        on (lineitem.l_discount >= lineitem.l_quantity)
      on (lineitem.l_tax <= lineitem.l_quantity)
    inner join nation
      inner join lineitem
        inner join nation
            inner join region
            on (nation.n_nationkey = region.r_regionkey )
          inner join lineitem
            inner join nation
              inner join orders
              on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
            on (orders.o_orderstatus > lineitem.l_linestatus)
          on (orders.o_totalprice < lineitem.l_quantity)
        on (lineitem.l_linestatus = nation.n_name)
      on (lineitem.l_shipdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
    on (region.r_regionkey >= orders.o_orderkey)
where lineitem.l_linenumber >= nation.n_nationkey
limit 100;

select

from

          inner join lineitem
          on (customer.c_acctbal < lineitem.l_extendedprice)
        inner join supplier
        on (lineitem.l_tax >= supplier.s_acctbal)
      inner join customer
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_receiptdate = lineitem.l_commitdate)
      on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct < lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
    inner join lineitem
        inner join orders
            inner join region
            on (orders.o_shippriority = orders.o_shippriority)
          inner join customer
          on (orders.o_shippriority = customer.c_custkey )
        on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct = customer.c_phone )
      inner join lineitem
        inner join part
          inner join lineitem
              inner join partsupp
              on (lineitem.l_extendedprice >= lineitem.l_discount)
            inner join region
            on (partsupp.ps_supplycost < lineitem.l_discount)
          on (part.p_type = region.r_comment )
        on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
      on (lineitem.l_partkey > region.r_regionkey)
    on (lineitem.l_shipmode is NULL)
where lineitem.l_orderkey is NULL

select distinct 
  nation.n_nationkey
from 
  supplier
    inner join nation
      inner join supplier
        inner join lineitem
          inner join orders
              inner join lineitem
              on (lineitem.l_orderkey = lineitem.l_partkey)
            inner join part
                inner join partsupp
                on (part.p_size = partsupp.ps_partkey )
              inner join customer
                inner join lineitem
                  inner join nation
                  on (lineitem.l_linenumber > nation.n_regionkey)
                on (customer.c_nationkey <= lineitem.l_linenumber)
              on (part.p_partkey = customer.c_custkey)
            on (orders.o_totalprice = partsupp.ps_supplycost )
          on (lineitem.l_tax > lineitem.l_quantity)
        on (supplier.s_acctbal = lineitem.l_discount)

select

    cast(supplier.s_name as bpchar)),

from

    inner join supplier
      inner join lineitem
          inner join partsupp
              inner join region
                inner join customer
                on (customer.c_custkey > region.r_regionkey)

            inner join nation

          on (lineitem.l_commitdate >= lineitem.l_receiptdate)

          inner join partsupp

        on (partsupp.ps_suppkey >= partsupp.ps_availqty)

where partsupp.ps_availqty is NULL

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  customer.c_address, 
  supplier.s_name, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty
from 
  supplier
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_partkey > supplier.s_suppkey)
          inner join supplier
          on (lineitem.l_receiptdate < lineitem.l_shipdate)
        inner join region
              inner join partsupp
              on (partsupp.ps_availqty = region.r_regionkey)
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_orderdate > orders.o_orderdate)
          inner join region
            inner join nation
              inner join supplier
              on (supplier.s_acctbal > supplier.s_acctbal)
            on (region.r_name > region.r_name)
          on (orders.o_shippriority < region.r_regionkey)
        on (lineitem.l_linestatus <= lineitem.l_linestatus)
      inner join orders
        inner join part
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_shipdate <= lineitem.l_shipdate)
          inner join nation
          on (lineitem.l_discount >= lineitem.l_discount)
        on (lineitem.l_receiptdate = lineitem.l_commitdate)
      on (supplier.s_nationkey = nation.n_regionkey)
    inner join customer
        inner join customer
        on (customer.c_mktsegment <= customer.c_phone)
      inner join supplier
      on (customer.c_acctbal > customer.c_acctbal)
    on (supplier.s_phone = supplier.s_name )
where nation.n_regionkey is not NULL;

sql:
select

  customer.c_address, 
  lineitem.l_partkey, 
  lineitem.l_quantity, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  part.p_name
from 
  customer
            inner join region
            on (customer.c_phone = region.r_name)
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_extendedprice >= lineitem.l_tax)
        inner join nation
        on (lineitem.l_returnflag >= lineitem.l_linestatus)
      inner join nation
              inner join customer
              on (nation.n_name < customer.c_mktsegment)
            inner join partsupp
            on (customer.c_mktsegment < customer.c_mktsegment)
          inner join lineitem
              inner join customer
                inner join supplier
                on (customer.c_acctbal < customer.c_acctbal)
              on (lineitem.l_tax <= customer.c_acctbal)
            inner join orders
            on (lineitem.l_discount <= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
          on (supplier.s_nationkey >= customer.c_nationkey)
        inner join part
        on (part.p_size > nation.n_nationkey)
      on (lineitem.l_commitdate > lineitem.l_commitdate)
    inner join partsupp
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_quantity >= lineitem.l_tax)
          inner join lineitem
          on (partsupp.ps_partkey = lineitem.l_orderkey )
        inner join customer
            inner join lineitem
            on (customer.c_name = lineitem.l_comment )
          inner join partsupp
          on (lineitem.l_returnflag <= customer.c_mktsegment)
        on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
      inner join orders
      on (lineitem.l_returnflag > orders.o_orderpriority)
    on (customer.c_acctbal is NULL)
where partsupp.ps_availqty is not NULL

            inner join nation
            on (partsupp.ps_supplycost <= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
          on (nation.n_name = nation.n_name)
        inner join region
        on (partsupp.ps_supplycost < partsupp.ps_supplycost)
      on (customer.c_comment = nation.n_comment )
    inner join lineitem
          inner join orders
            inner join region
            on (region.r_name >= orders.o_orderstatus)
          on (lineitem.l_suppkey >= lineitem.l_linenumber)
        inner join customer
        on (lineitem.l_partkey >= lineitem.l_linenumber)
      inner join customer
        inner join partsupp
        on (customer.c_phone = customer.c_mktsegment)
      on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_commitdate)
    on (region.r_regionkey is not NULL)
where orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate
limit 118;
nl: What are the brands of parts supplied by suppliers in a region where the order status is high?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  lineitem.l_partkey, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  avg(
    cast(partsupp.ps_supplycost as "numeric")), 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  lineitem.l_shipdate
from 
  lineitem
    inner join region
      inner join partsupp
      on (partsupp.ps_supplycost > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
    on (lineitem.l_extendedprice = partsupp.ps_supplycost )
where region.r_comment is NULL
limit 113;
nl: What are the commit dates, regions, maximum null values, part keys, minimum intervals, supply costs, line statuses, available quantities, and ship dates for orders that have no comments?

sql:
select

    cast(supplier.s_name as bpchar)),

  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  supplier.s_name
from 
  supplier
    inner join region
      inner join supplier
      on (region.r_name = supplier.s_name )
    on (supplier.s_name = region.r_name )
where supplier.s_phone is NULL
limit 73;
nl: What are the names of regions, along with their total count, minimum supplier name, and key information about suppliers in each region where there's no phone number?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  part.p_brand, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  orders.o_orderkey, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  part.p_type, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  lineitem.l_orderkey, 
  customer.c_acctbal, 
  customer.c_phone
from 
  lineitem
          inner join supplier
          on (lineitem.l_discount > lineitem.l_tax)
        inner join customer
          inner join region
          on (customer.c_name = region.r_comment )
        on (lineitem.l_tax <= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
      inner join orders
          inner join customer
              inner join supplier
              on (customer.c_acctbal = customer.c_acctbal)
            inner join customer
              inner join part
                inner join lineitem
                on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_commitdate)
              on (lineitem.l_receiptdate = lineitem.l_commitdate)
            on (lineitem.l_tax >= lineitem.l_quantity)
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate < lineitem.l_shipdate)
        inner join part
        on (supplier.s_nationkey = customer.c_custkey)
      on (supplier.s_acctbal >= orders.o_totalprice)
    inner join partsupp
    on (region.r_name is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_orderkey is not NULL
limit 105;
nl: What are the account balances, brands, regions, supply costs, commit dates, order keys, phone numbers, types, nation keys, and account balances of customers who have placed orders with a total price greater than or equal to their account balance?

    cast(cast(null as pg_lsn) as pg_lsn))
from

    on (supplier.s_acctbal > supplier.s_acctbal)
where supplier.s_name is NULL
limit 122;

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  customer.c_comment
from 
  supplier
        inner join customer
          inner join partsupp
              inner join partsupp
              on (partsupp.ps_supplycost > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
            inner join partsupp
            on (partsupp.ps_comment = partsupp.ps_comment )
          on (customer.c_acctbal = partsupp.ps_supplycost )
        on (customer.c_acctbal <= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
      inner join customer
        inner join partsupp
          inner join part
          on (part.p_size <= partsupp.ps_partkey)
        on (part.p_partkey < partsupp.ps_availqty)
      on (part.p_container < customer.c_mktsegment)
    inner join supplier
        inner join part
        on (supplier.s_phone <= supplier.s_name)
      inner join lineitem
        inner join orders
          inner join orders
          on (orders.o_custkey = orders.o_custkey)
        on (lineitem.l_quantity = orders.o_totalprice )
      on (lineitem.l_partkey >= supplier.s_nationkey)
    on (partsupp.ps_comment is not NULL)
where partsupp.ps_partkey is NULL
limit 108;
nl: What are the supplier keys and customer comments for suppliers who supply parts with high supply costs, where the supply cost matches the account balance, and the part size is less than or equal to the available quantity?

sql:
select

  customer.c_acctbal, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  orders.o_orderstatus
from 
  orders
            inner join lineitem
              inner join orders
              on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct > orders.o_orderstatus)
            on (lineitem.l_extendedprice >= lineitem.l_discount)
          inner join part
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_custkey <= customer.c_nationkey)
          on (part.p_mfgr > orders.o_clerk)
        inner join lineitem
          inner join supplier
          on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
        on (customer.c_acctbal <= lineitem.l_discount)
      inner join lineitem
      on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct < lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
    inner join orders
      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_totalprice > orders.o_totalprice)
    on (lineitem.l_quantity is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_linestatus <= orders.o_clerk
limit 67;
