        on (lineitem.l_discount <= supplier.s_acctbal)
      inner join nation
        inner join orders
        on (nation.n_regionkey > nation.n_regionkey)
      on (supplier.s_nationkey >= lineitem.l_partkey)
    on (region.r_comment = region.r_comment )
where lineitem.l_commitdate is NULL;
nl: What are the comments and details about suppliers, parts, regions, and orders that have no commitment date?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_tax, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money))
from 
  nation
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_shipdate)
      inner join part
      on (nation.n_comment = part.p_name )
    inner join partsupp
      inner join part
        inner join orders
        on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
      on (orders.o_orderkey < orders.o_shippriority)
    on (part.p_comment is not NULL)
where part.p_partkey is NULL
limit 95;
nl: What are the tax rates, part numbers, and total amounts for all line items with no shipping priority?

sql:
select  
  part.p_retailprice, 
  part.p_name, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "time") as "time")), 
  part.p_type, 
  part.p_container, 
  part.p_comment, 
  part.p_container
from 
  part
where part.p_size is NULL
limit 158;
nl: What are the retail prices, names, and maximum time values for all parts that have no size, along with their types, containers, comments, and container details?

sql:
select  
  min(
    cast(cast(null as anyenum) as anyenum)), 
  supplier.s_address, 
  region.r_comment, 
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  nation.n_comment
from 
  orders
      inner join lineitem
          inner join partsupp
              inner join nation
              on (nation.n_name = nation.n_name)
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_tax > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
          on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_commitdate)
        inner join supplier
        on (partsupp.ps_partkey > lineitem.l_partkey)
      on (lineitem.l_shipmode <= lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
    inner join nation
      inner join region
      on (nation.n_regionkey > nation.n_nationkey)
    on (nation.n_regionkey is NULL)
where nation.n_name is not NULL;
nl: What are the minimum, supplier addresses, region comments, and other details for orders that have a specific shipping date, tax rate, and receipt date?

sql:
select distinct 
  supplier.s_name, 
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  supplier.s_name, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as anyenum) as anyenum)), 
  supplier.s_address, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  supplier.s_name, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  supplier.s_address
from 
  supplier
where supplier.s_nationkey is NULL;
nl: What are the names and details of suppliers from a specific nation that have no nation key?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_comment, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  nation.n_nationkey
from 
  supplier
        inner join region
        on (supplier.s_nationkey = region.r_regionkey )
      inner join nation
      on (supplier.s_suppkey >= supplier.s_suppkey)
    inner join nation
          inner join customer
            inner join supplier
            on (customer.c_custkey < supplier.s_suppkey)
          on (supplier.s_acctbal > supplier.s_acctbal)
        inner join customer
        on (supplier.s_phone > customer.c_phone)
      inner join partsupp
          inner join lineitem
          on (partsupp.ps_supplycost >= lineitem.l_tax)
        inner join nation
        on (lineitem.l_extendedprice > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
      on (customer.c_mktsegment = lineitem.l_returnflag )
    on (region.r_comment is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_returnflag is NULL
limit 116;
nl: What are the supplier comments, average time intervals, and other details for suppliers that have a certain balance, nation key, available parts quantity, and phone number, along with their customers' nation keys?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_name, 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate
from 
  supplier
    inner join region
      inner join supplier
        inner join lineitem
        on (supplier.s_suppkey = lineitem.l_linenumber)
      on (lineitem.l_discount = lineitem.l_tax)
    on (lineitem.l_shipdate = lineitem.l_receiptdate)
where lineitem.l_commitdate > lineitem.l_receiptdate
limit 147;
nl: What are the nation keys, names of suppliers, and receipt dates for orders that were shipped after they were received?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  customer.c_acctbal, 
  lineitem.l_orderkey, 
  lineitem.l_extendedprice, 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  lineitem.l_comment, 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  customer.c_name
from 
  customer
    inner join lineitem
    on (customer.c_custkey = customer.c_nationkey)
where customer.c_acctbal is NULL;
nl: What are the details of orders with no outstanding balance from customers who have not paid their account?

sql:
select  
  min(
    cast(lineitem.l_discount as "numeric")), 
  orders.o_comment, 
  orders.o_custkey, 
  lineitem.l_discount, 
  lineitem.l_quantity, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as inet) as inet)), 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  lineitem.l_discount, 
  lineitem.l_partkey, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as timetz) as timetz)), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  orders.o_orderpriority, 
  lineitem.l_comment
from 
  orders
    inner join lineitem
    on (orders.o_orderstatus is NULL)
where orders.o_totalprice is not NULL
limit 38;
nl: What are the minimum discount, customer comments, and order details for orders with a total price that is not null?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  lineitem.l_suppkey, 
  lineitem.l_suppkey, 
  part.p_size, 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  customer.c_address, 
  part.p_retailprice, 
  part.p_type, 
  part.p_name, 
  orders.o_comment, 
  lineitem.l_partkey
from 
  lineitem
      inner join orders
            inner join part
              inner join lineitem
              on (lineitem.l_returnflag < part.p_brand)
            on (orders.o_clerk = orders.o_orderstatus)
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct <= lineitem.l_shipmode)
        inner join customer
              inner join part
              on (customer.c_mktsegment > customer.c_mktsegment)
            inner join nation
            on (customer.c_comment = nation.n_comment )
          inner join part
                inner join supplier
                on (part.p_retailprice = supplier.s_acctbal)
              inner join orders
              on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
            inner join customer
            on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
          on (nation.n_nationkey <= part.p_size)
        on (lineitem.l_commitdate < orders.o_orderdate)
      on (orders.o_orderdate = lineitem.l_commitdate)
    inner join part
      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate)
    on (part.p_name is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_returnflag is NULL
limit 116;
nl: What are the order dates, supplier keys, part sizes, return flags, customer addresses, retail prices, types, names, and comments for all orders that have a specific combination of characteristics?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_acctbal, 
  customer.c_comment, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as "timestamp") as "timestamp")), 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "time") as "time")), 
  customer.c_mktsegment
from 
  customer
where customer.c_phone is not NULL;
nl: What are the outstanding balances, comments, earliest and latest phone activity times, and market segments for customers with a valid phone number?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_address, 
  customer.c_address, 
  customer.c_address, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as timestamptz) as timestamptz)), 
  customer.c_mktsegment
from 
  customer
where customer.c_nationkey is not NULL
limit 179;
nl: What are the addresses and market segments of customers, along with their maximum timestamp, excluding those without a nation key?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_orderstatus, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  orders.o_shippriority
from 
  partsupp
    inner join nation
      inner join part
        inner join orders
          inner join region
            inner join nation
            on (nation.n_nationkey < nation.n_regionkey)
          on (orders.o_totalprice >= orders.o_totalprice)
        on (part.p_mfgr >= nation.n_name)
      on (orders.o_orderdate <= orders.o_orderdate)
    on (region.r_comment is NULL)
where part.p_brand is NULL;
nl: What are the order statuses, average value, regions, comments, and shipping priorities for all orders with no brand?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_comment
from 
  partsupp
where partsupp.ps_partkey is NULL;
nl: What are the supplier keys and comments for suppliers that do not supply any parts?

sql:
select  
  region.r_name, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey
from 
  region
    inner join supplier
          inner join nation
              inner join partsupp
              on (nation.n_name > nation.n_name)
            inner join region
            on (partsupp.ps_availqty > partsupp.ps_partkey)
          on (supplier.s_acctbal <= supplier.s_acctbal)
        inner join partsupp
        on (supplier.s_name >= region.r_name)
      inner join supplier
        inner join supplier
        on (supplier.s_nationkey < supplier.s_suppkey)
      on (supplier.s_phone < supplier.s_name)
    on (partsupp.ps_comment is NULL)
where supplier.s_acctbal is not NULL
limit 108;
nl: What are the names, region keys, and nation keys of all regions where a supplier has an account balance that is not null?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_comment, 
  customer.c_name
from 
  supplier
      inner join region
            inner join partsupp
            on (region.r_comment = partsupp.ps_comment )
          inner join customer
          on (region.r_name = customer.c_phone )
        inner join customer
        on (region.r_name < customer.c_mktsegment)
      on (supplier.s_nationkey < partsupp.ps_partkey)
    inner join customer
    on (partsupp.ps_suppkey is NULL)
where customer.c_custkey is NULL
limit 38;
nl: What are the comments from suppliers that have no part supplies, along with the names of customers who do not exist in a specific market segment?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_clerk, 
  region.r_name
from 
  nation
          inner join part
          on (part.p_size > nation.n_regionkey)
        inner join orders
        on (part.p_brand = orders.o_orderstatus )
      inner join region
      on (part.p_mfgr = region.r_name )
    inner join partsupp
      inner join partsupp
            inner join region
              inner join region
              on (region.r_name > region.r_name)
            on (partsupp.ps_suppkey <= partsupp.ps_partkey)
          inner join part
          on (region.r_regionkey < region.r_regionkey)
        inner join region
        on (partsupp.ps_supplycost > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
      on (part.p_container <= region.r_name)
    on (part.p_type is not NULL)
where part.p_retailprice < partsupp.ps_supplycost;
nl: What are the names of the regions and the clerks who handle orders for products that have a retail price less than their supply cost?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_custkey
from 
  lineitem
        inner join region
          inner join partsupp
          on (partsupp.ps_supplycost = partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_receiptdate)
      inner join customer
        inner join customer
        on (customer.c_acctbal > customer.c_acctbal)
      on (customer.c_mktsegment > region.r_name)
    inner join part
      inner join nation
      on (part.p_comment = nation.n_comment )
    on (customer.c_phone is NULL)
where partsupp.ps_partkey is not NULL
limit 105;
nl: What are the customer IDs of customers who have a higher account balance than others, live in a region where the supply cost is high, and have never made a phone call?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_name, 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate
from 
  lineitem
      inner join supplier
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_linenumber < lineitem.l_suppkey)
      on (lineitem.l_returnflag <= lineitem.l_shipmode)
    inner join customer
      inner join part
        inner join lineitem
        on (part.p_container = lineitem.l_returnflag )
      on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_receiptdate)
    on (lineitem.l_comment = part.p_name )
where lineitem.l_extendedprice is not NULL;
nl: What are the names of customers who have received products with a receipt date, and what were those dates?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_phone, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_name, 
  region.r_name
from 
  customer
          inner join nation
          on (customer.c_acctbal = customer.c_acctbal)
        inner join region
        on (customer.c_custkey >= customer.c_nationkey)
      inner join nation
      on (customer.c_acctbal = customer.c_acctbal)
    inner join part
    on (customer.c_mktsegment is not NULL)
where nation.n_regionkey > nation.n_nationkey
limit 83;
nl: What are the phone numbers, nation keys, and region names of customers who have a certain balance in their account, live in a specific nation, and belong to a particular market segment?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_name
from 
  nation
      inner join customer
      on (customer.c_custkey >= customer.c_custkey)
    inner join supplier
      inner join supplier
      on (supplier.s_acctbal = supplier.s_acctbal)
    on (customer.c_name is not NULL)
where supplier.s_suppkey is not NULL;
nl: What are the names of suppliers that have customers with non-null customer names?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_nationkey
from 
  nation
where nation.n_comment is not NULL
limit 137;
nl: What are the nation keys for countries with a comment?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_supplycost
from 
  partsupp
    inner join supplier
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_orderkey <= supplier.s_nationkey)
      inner join region
      on (lineitem.l_commitdate > lineitem.l_receiptdate)
    on (lineitem.l_suppkey is NULL)
where supplier.s_acctbal is not NULL;
nl: What are the supply costs for suppliers who have no orders in their account?

sql:
select  
  region.r_regionkey, 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  max(
    cast(lineitem.l_commitdate as date)), 
  region.r_name
from 
  partsupp
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_shipmode < lineitem.l_returnflag)
      inner join region
      on (lineitem.l_commitdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
    inner join supplier
    on (partsupp.ps_availqty is NULL)
where lineitem.l_comment is not NULL;
nl: What are the region names, phone numbers of suppliers, part keys, comments, and maximum time gaps for orders that have been shipped but not returned, along with the latest shipment dates?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  lineitem.l_partkey, 
  lineitem.l_shipmode, 
  lineitem.l_partkey, 
  lineitem.l_orderkey
from 
  lineitem
where lineitem.l_returnflag is NULL;
nl: What are the commit dates, part keys, shipping modes, and order keys for all orders that were not returned?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_name, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as anyenum) as anyenum)), 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as anyarray) as anyarray)), 
  customer.c_phone, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as anyarray) as anyarray)), 
  min(
    cast(customer.c_mktsegment as bpchar)), 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as oid) as oid)), 
  customer.c_name, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  customer.c_comment, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  customer.c_mktsegment
from 
  customer
where customer.c_address is NULL;
nl: What are the names of customers with no address, along with their phone numbers, nation keys, market segments, and comments?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as xid8) as xid8)), 
  lineitem.l_orderkey, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey
from 
  customer
        inner join lineitem
          inner join nation
            inner join partsupp
            on (nation.n_regionkey = partsupp.ps_partkey )
          on (lineitem.l_linestatus >= lineitem.l_shipmode)
        on (lineitem.l_partkey <= partsupp.ps_suppkey)
      inner join region
          inner join nation
          on (region.r_regionkey = nation.n_nationkey )
        inner join lineitem
            inner join part
            on (lineitem.l_partkey = part.p_partkey )
          inner join nation
          on (lineitem.l_discount <= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
        on (nation.n_name = lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
      on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct < nation.n_name)
    inner join customer
    on (customer.c_nationkey is NULL)
where partsupp.ps_supplycost < lineitem.l_extendedprice
limit 69;
nl: What are the return flags, maximum values, order keys, and supplier keys for customers who do not have a specific nation key?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_address, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  supplier.s_name, 
  avg(
    cast(supplier.s_acctbal as "numeric"))
from 
  supplier
where supplier.s_name is NULL;
nl: What are the addresses and average account balances of suppliers with no name?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey
from 
  nation
where nation.n_comment is not NULL
limit 24;
nl: What are the details of each nation, including its comment and region key, where there is a comment provided?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_address, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as inet) as inet)), 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8)), 
  supplier.s_name
from 
  supplier
where supplier.s_acctbal > supplier.s_acctbal;
nl: What is the address, comment, and name of each supplier who has a higher account balance than their current account balance?

sql:
select  
  part.p_container, 
  part.p_container, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  part.p_size, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  part.p_mfgr, 
  part.p_mfgr, 
  max(
    cast(lineitem.l_receiptdate as date))
from 
  part
            inner join customer
            on (part.p_comment = customer.c_name )
          inner join part
            inner join lineitem
            on (part.p_comment = lineitem.l_comment )
          on (customer.c_address = part.p_name )
        inner join supplier
        on (customer.c_address = supplier.s_address )
      inner join supplier
        inner join part
        on (supplier.s_acctbal > supplier.s_acctbal)
      on (supplier.s_phone >= part.p_mfgr)
    inner join part
          inner join part
              inner join customer
              on (customer.c_custkey <= part.p_partkey)
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_orderpriority > customer.c_phone)
          on (customer.c_acctbal > orders.o_totalprice)
        inner join part
            inner join part
                inner join part
                on (part.p_brand > part.p_mfgr)
              inner join region
              on (part.p_brand = part.p_brand)
            on (part.p_partkey <= part.p_partkey)
          inner join region
          on (part.p_brand >= part.p_brand)
        on (region.r_regionkey < orders.o_custkey)
      inner join part
        inner join nation
        on (part.p_retailprice = part.p_retailprice)
      on (orders.o_orderdate > orders.o_orderdate)
    on (part.p_name = customer.c_name )
where part.p_type is NULL;
nl: What are the unique combinations of container, size, manufacturer, and region, along with the average receipt date, maximum order date, and total price for each combination?

sql:
select distinct 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as timestamptz) as timestamptz)), 
  part.p_container, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  part.p_container, 
  part.p_brand, 
  part.p_container, 
  part.p_retailprice
from 
  part
where part.p_mfgr <= part.p_mfgr;
nl: What are the minimum and maximum values of null, along with the average value of another null, grouped by p_container, p_brand, and retail price?

sql:
select  
  part.p_type, 
  part.p_size, 
  part.p_size, 
  part.p_retailprice
from 
  part
where part.p_size is NULL;
nl: What types of parts are there that have no size?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as pg_lsn) as pg_lsn)), 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost
from 
  partsupp
where partsupp.ps_supplycost is not NULL;
nl: What are the part keys, supply costs, available quantities, and comments for all suppliers that have non-null supply costs?

sql:
select  
  region.r_name
from 
  partsupp
    inner join region
    on (partsupp.ps_partkey is not NULL)
where partsupp.ps_availqty is NULL;
nl: What are the names of regions where there are no available quantities?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  nation.n_name, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as inet) as inet)), 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_name
from 
  nation
where nation.n_name = nation.n_name
limit 166;
nl: What are the details of each nation, including its region key and name, along with a maximum value?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_discount, 
  part.p_type, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  part.p_name, 
  part.p_size, 
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  lineitem.l_suppkey
from 
  part
    inner join orders
        inner join partsupp
            inner join lineitem
              inner join customer
                inner join part
                on (part.p_container < customer.c_mktsegment)
              on (lineitem.l_discount = part.p_retailprice )
            on (lineitem.l_discount > lineitem.l_extendedprice)
          inner join orders
          on (customer.c_mktsegment < lineitem.l_returnflag)
        on (orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate)
      inner join supplier
      on (lineitem.l_discount < lineitem.l_extendedprice)
    on (part.p_retailprice = orders.o_totalprice )
where partsupp.ps_suppkey is NULL
limit 56;
nl: What are the discount rates, product types, account balances, comments, names, sizes, total prices, and supplier information for customers who purchase specific products with a certain market segment, where the discount rate exceeds the extended price?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey
from 
  supplier
    inner join nation
    on (nation.n_comment is not NULL)
where nation.n_name <= supplier.s_name
limit 182;
nl: What are the region keys and nation keys of nations with a comment that have names less than or equal to the name of their corresponding suppliers, along with how many such nations there are?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_name, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  nation.n_name
from 
  supplier
    inner join nation
    on (supplier.s_acctbal < supplier.s_acctbal)
where nation.n_nationkey is NULL;
nl: What are the names of nations with no account balance and their corresponding suppliers' account balances?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_supplycost
from 
  partsupp
where partsupp.ps_partkey is NULL;
nl: What is the supply cost for all parts that have no part key?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_phone, 
  count(*), 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as tid) as tid)), 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  customer.c_comment, 
  supplier.s_name
from 
  supplier
    inner join customer
    on (customer.c_name is not NULL)
where customer.c_nationkey is NULL;
nl: What are the phone numbers of customers who have no nation key, along with how many such customers there are, their average rating, minimum rating, and other details like supplier names, comments, and nation keys?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  region.r_name, 
  lineitem.l_partkey, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  region.r_name, 
  supplier.s_phone
from 
  region
      inner join supplier
      on (supplier.s_phone < region.r_name)
    inner join lineitem
    on (lineitem.l_orderkey is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_partkey is not NULL
limit 180;
nl: What are the receipt dates, regions, part numbers, and phone numbers of suppliers who have shipped parts to orders with non-null order keys, sorted by a specific limit?

sql:
select  
  part.p_mfgr, 
  part.p_partkey, 
  part.p_container, 
  part.p_brand, 
  part.p_brand, 
  lineitem.l_suppkey, 
  lineitem.l_partkey, 
  part.p_container, 
  lineitem.l_orderkey
from 
  lineitem
    inner join part
    on (lineitem.l_comment is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_linenumber is not NULL
limit 188;
nl: What are the manufacturer, part key, container type, brand, and supplier information for orders with comments?

sql:
select  
  region.r_comment, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as oid) as oid)), 
  region.r_regionkey
from 
  region
    inner join supplier
    on (region.r_comment is not NULL)
where region.r_comment is not NULL;
nl: What are the comments for each region, along with the nation key and a count of all records, grouped by region?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  lineitem.l_suppkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  lineitem.l_discount
from 
  lineitem
where lineitem.l_shipinstruct is NULL;
nl: What are the linenumber, supplier key, maximum value, and discount for each line item that has no shipping instruction?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_name, 
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  lineitem.l_shipdate
from 
  nation
    inner join lineitem
    on (lineitem.l_linestatus is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_shipdate is NULL
limit 56;
nl: What are the names of nations that have shipped nothing yet, along with their latest and committed dates?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_name, 
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  orders.o_orderkey
from 
  nation
    inner join orders
    on (orders.o_totalprice = orders.o_totalprice)
where orders.o_custkey is not NULL
limit 89;
nl: What are the names of nations, their comments, total prices, and order keys for customers who have placed orders?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_shipmode, 
  lineitem.l_comment, 
  lineitem.l_tax, 
  lineitem.l_tax, 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  min(
    cast(lineitem.l_orderkey as int4)), 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money)), 
  lineitem.l_orderkey, 
  lineitem.l_tax, 
  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct
from 
  lineitem
where lineitem.l_shipmode > lineitem.l_linestatus
limit 154;
nl: What are the shipping modes, comments, taxes, and statuses of orders that have been shipped in a way that doesn't match their status, along with the earliest order key, shipping instructions, return flags, receipt dates, and ship dates?

sql:
select  
  avg(
    cast(lineitem.l_linenumber as int4)), 
  lineitem.l_quantity, 
  part.p_brand, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "time") as "time")), 
  part.p_brand, 
  part.p_container
from 
  part
    inner join lineitem
      inner join lineitem
      on (lineitem.l_orderkey = lineitem.l_linenumber)
    on (part.p_type is NULL)
where part.p_type is NULL;
nl: What is the average linenumber, quantity of each item, and brand for all items that have no type?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_comment, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2))
from 
  nation
        inner join partsupp
          inner join customer
          on (customer.c_mktsegment = customer.c_phone)
        on (customer.c_mktsegment > customer.c_phone)
      inner join region
        inner join nation
        on (nation.n_name >= nation.n_name)
      on (nation.n_name >= nation.n_name)
    inner join part
    on (region.r_comment = part.p_name )
where partsupp.ps_partkey is not NULL
limit 121;
nl: What are the comments from each nation, along with their corresponding customer phone numbers, and what is the minimum value for all these combinations?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  supplier.s_address, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  supplier.s_name
from 
  supplier
where supplier.s_acctbal is not NULL
limit 39;
nl: What are the details of all suppliers with non-zero account balances?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  orders.o_shippriority
from 
  orders
where orders.o_orderdate is NULL
limit 103;
nl: What are the total prices, order dates, and shipping priorities of all orders with no specified delivery date?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  lineitem.l_extendedprice, 
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  lineitem.l_suppkey, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money)), 
  min(
    cast(lineitem.l_partkey as int4)), 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as timetz) as timetz)), 
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as anyarray) as anyarray)), 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  lineitem.l_extendedprice, 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct
from 
  partsupp
    inner join lineitem
    on (partsupp.ps_availqty is NULL)
where partsupp.ps_partkey is NULL
limit 112;
nl: What are the instructions for shipping, extended prices, and dates for all line items with no available quantity or part key?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2))
from 
  partsupp
    inner join orders
    on (orders.o_clerk is not NULL)
where orders.o_shippriority >= partsupp.ps_partkey;
nl: What are the supplier key and available quantity for each part, along with the minimum value?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  nation.n_name, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  nation.n_regionkey
from 
  partsupp
    inner join nation
    on (partsupp.ps_supplycost > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
where partsupp.ps_supplycost is not NULL
limit 124;
nl: What are the details of each region, including its name and comment, for regions where supply costs are unusually high?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_comment
from 
  region
        inner join region
        on (region.r_name = region.r_name )
      inner join partsupp
        inner join nation
                inner join region
                on (nation.n_name > nation.n_name)
              inner join supplier
              on (nation.n_name = supplier.s_name )
            inner join supplier
            on (nation.n_regionkey < nation.n_nationkey)
          inner join part
              inner join part
              on (part.p_partkey = part.p_partkey)
            inner join supplier
            on (part.p_retailprice <= supplier.s_acctbal)
          on (supplier.s_acctbal >= supplier.s_acctbal)
        on (partsupp.ps_suppkey = nation.n_nationkey )
      on (part.p_retailprice < supplier.s_acctbal)
    inner join region
      inner join nation
      on (nation.n_name >= nation.n_name)
    on (part.p_container < supplier.s_name)
where supplier.s_nationkey is NULL;
nl: What are the supplier keys, nation keys, and comments for suppliers that do not have a specific nation associated with them?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  orders.o_orderkey, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as xid8) as xid8)), 
  supplier.s_address
from 
  supplier
    inner join lineitem
            inner join nation
            on (lineitem.l_comment = nation.n_comment )
          inner join part
          on (lineitem.l_receiptdate < lineitem.l_commitdate)
        inner join orders
        on (lineitem.l_linestatus = orders.o_orderstatus)
      inner join partsupp
      on (orders.o_shippriority = partsupp.ps_partkey )
    on (supplier.s_name > part.p_mfgr)
where part.p_mfgr is NULL
limit 134;
nl: What are the part numbers, order keys, earliest possible IDs, and supplier addresses for all orders that have not been committed yet?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  lineitem.l_shipmode, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_name, 
  lineitem.l_orderkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_regionkey
from 
  nation
    inner join lineitem
    on (lineitem.l_shipmode is NULL)
where lineitem.l_extendedprice is NULL
limit 38;
nl: What are the nation keys, ship dates, and comments for nations with no shipping mode or extended price, along with their region key?

sql:
select  
  part.p_name, 
  part.p_retailprice, 
  avg(
    cast(part.p_retailprice as "numeric")), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as timetz) as timetz)), 
  part.p_retailprice
from 
  part
where part.p_container is NULL
limit 25;
nl: What are the names, retail prices, average retail price, minimum time, and retail prices of parts that have no container, along with their details?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as oid) as oid)), 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_regionkey
from 
  nation
    inner join nation
    on (nation.n_name is not NULL)
where nation.n_name is NULL
limit 99;
nl: What are the names of nations with no comment, along with their keys and regions?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  lineitem.l_comment, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  region.r_comment, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as "timestamp") as "timestamp")), 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  part.p_brand, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  customer.c_name
from 
  customer
        inner join customer
        on (customer.c_phone <= customer.c_mktsegment)
      inner join part
          inner join part
            inner join lineitem
            on (part.p_container >= part.p_brand)
          on (lineitem.l_tax >= lineitem.l_tax)
        inner join orders
          inner join region
          on (region.r_regionkey = orders.o_custkey)
        on (part.p_comment = region.r_comment )
      on (customer.c_mktsegment = lineitem.l_linestatus)
    inner join nation
        inner join customer
          inner join supplier
          on (customer.c_acctbal = supplier.s_acctbal)
        on (supplier.s_phone < customer.c_phone)
      inner join part
          inner join part
          on (part.p_partkey = part.p_partkey)
        inner join region
        on (part.p_brand = part.p_brand)
      on (customer.c_custkey = part.p_size)
    on (orders.o_orderdate >= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
where part.p_name is NULL;
nl: What are the market segments, comments about customers, nations, regions, and parts that have no name?

sql:
select  
  region.r_name, 
  region.r_name, 
  region.r_comment, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  region.r_comment, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  region.r_comment, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  region.r_name, 
  region.r_comment, 
  region.r_name, 
  region.r_name
from 
  region
where region.r_comment is not NULL
limit 98;
nl: What are the names, comments, and region keys for regions with a comment, along with their repetition counts?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as anyenum) as anyenum)), 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8))
from 
  partsupp
where partsupp.ps_suppkey is NULL
limit 91;
nl: What are the comments, part keys, and supply costs for all suppliers with no supplier key, along with any additional information?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  region.r_comment, 
  region.r_comment, 
  sum(
    cast(supplier.s_suppkey as int4)), 
  supplier.s_address, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  region.r_name
from 
  supplier
      inner join part
        inner join orders
          inner join nation
          on (orders.o_totalprice >= orders.o_totalprice)
        on (orders.o_totalprice > orders.o_totalprice)
      on (supplier.s_acctbal = orders.o_totalprice )
    inner join region
        inner join supplier
            inner join nation
            on (supplier.s_acctbal < supplier.s_acctbal)
          inner join region
          on (supplier.s_suppkey = supplier.s_suppkey)
        on (supplier.s_acctbal = supplier.s_acctbal)
      inner join supplier
      on (region.r_regionkey <= supplier.s_nationkey)
    on (orders.o_orderkey = region.r_regionkey )
where nation.n_nationkey is not NULL;
nl: What are the supplier keys, region comments, and total number of suppliers for each region that have a balance greater than their total price?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  nation.n_name
from 
  supplier
            inner join lineitem
            on (supplier.s_phone = lineitem.l_returnflag )
          inner join part
              inner join orders
                inner join partsupp
                on (orders.o_comment = partsupp.ps_comment )
              on (orders.o_orderkey <= orders.o_shippriority)
            inner join orders
                inner join orders
                on (orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate)
              inner join customer
              on (orders.o_custkey >= customer.c_custkey)
            on (orders.o_shippriority < orders.o_shippriority)
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate < orders.o_orderdate)
        inner join partsupp
          inner join part
            inner join nation
            on (part.p_size < nation.n_nationkey)
          on (nation.n_nationkey <= part.p_size)
        on (orders.o_shippriority > customer.c_custkey)
      inner join region
      on (nation.n_regionkey = region.r_regionkey )
    inner join nation
    on (partsupp.ps_partkey <= orders.o_custkey)
where orders.o_orderpriority >= orders.o_orderstatus
limit 142;
nl: What is the total price of each order, and which country did it come from?

sql:
select  
  region.r_regionkey, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  part.p_container, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  region.r_name, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  part.p_partkey, 
  region.r_name, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost
from 
  partsupp
      inner join region
      on (region.r_regionkey <= partsupp.ps_partkey)
    inner join part
    on (region.r_regionkey is not NULL)
where part.p_retailprice = partsupp.ps_supplycost
limit 98;
nl: What are the region, part key, available quantity, and other details for each combination of regions and parts where the retail price matches the supply cost?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_comment, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as timetz) as timetz)), 
  customer.c_address
from 
  nation
              inner join region
              on (nation.n_regionkey > region.r_regionkey)
            inner join nation
            on (nation.n_name >= nation.n_name)
          inner join part
            inner join lineitem
            on (part.p_container > lineitem.l_linestatus)
          on (region.r_comment = lineitem.l_comment )
        inner join partsupp
          inner join nation
          on (partsupp.ps_partkey <= nation.n_nationkey)
        on (lineitem.l_quantity < lineitem.l_discount)
      inner join customer
      on (nation.n_name < nation.n_name)
    inner join lineitem
    on (partsupp.ps_availqty = lineitem.l_orderkey )
where nation.n_comment is not NULL;
nl: What are the comments for each nation, along with any maximum time and their addresses?

sql:
select  
  part.p_mfgr, 
  region.r_comment, 
  part.p_type, 
  part.p_brand, 
  part.p_name, 
  region.r_name, 
  part.p_mfgr, 
  region.r_regionkey
from 
  region
    inner join part
    on (part.p_retailprice is NULL)
where part.p_name is not NULL
limit 183;
nl: What are the manufacturer, comment, type, brand, and name of parts that have no retail price, along with their corresponding regions?

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(cast(null as bpchar) as bpchar)), 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost
from 
  partsupp
where partsupp.ps_supplycost is not NULL;
nl: What are the maximum and actual supply costs for all non-null records?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_comment, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as anyenum) as anyenum)), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  customer.c_address, 
  customer.c_custkey
from 
  customer
where customer.c_acctbal is NULL
limit 62;
nl: What are the comments, maximum value, minimum time interval, addresses, and IDs of customers with no outstanding balance?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_name, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as xid8) as xid8)), 
  region.r_name, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  min(
    cast(region.r_regionkey as int4)), 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  region.r_regionkey
from 
  region
    inner join nation
      inner join region
      on (region.r_name > nation.n_name)
    on (region.r_name = nation.n_name )
where region.r_regionkey < nation.n_regionkey
limit 190;
nl: What are the names of nations, their minimum and maximum intervals, regions, and key information for nations in a specific region where the nation name is less than the region name?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  nation.n_name, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  orders.o_orderkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as anyenum) as anyenum)), 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  orders.o_orderkey, 
  orders.o_orderkey, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  orders.o_orderstatus, 
  orders.o_comment, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8)), 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as text) as text))
from 
  orders
    inner join partsupp
      inner join nation
      on (nation.n_regionkey < partsupp.ps_availqty)
    on (orders.o_totalprice is NULL)
where nation.n_regionkey is not NULL
limit 30;
nl: What are the names of nations, their comments, and supply costs for orders with no total price?

sql:
select  
  part.p_mfgr, 
  part.p_brand
from 
  part
where part.p_retailprice is not NULL
limit 136;
nl: What are the manufacturer and brand of parts with a retail price, excluding those without a price?

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(lineitem.l_shipdate as date))
from 
  orders
      inner join lineitem
        inner join part
            inner join nation
            on (part.p_retailprice <= part.p_retailprice)
          inner join region
          on (nation.n_regionkey = region.r_regionkey )
        on (lineitem.l_tax = lineitem.l_discount)
      on (orders.o_custkey > orders.o_shippriority)
    inner join nation
        inner join partsupp
        on (partsupp.ps_supplycost < partsupp.ps_supplycost)
      inner join supplier
      on (supplier.s_phone = supplier.s_phone)
    on (supplier.s_comment is not NULL)
where supplier.s_nationkey is NULL;
nl: What is the latest date that a shipment was made?

sql:
select  
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval"))
from 
  region
      inner join part
        inner join nation
          inner join partsupp
            inner join supplier
              inner join customer
              on (supplier.s_phone >= supplier.s_name)
            on (supplier.s_nationkey >= customer.c_custkey)
          on (customer.c_acctbal >= customer.c_acctbal)
        on (customer.c_phone > supplier.s_phone)
      on (supplier.s_suppkey >= supplier.s_suppkey)
    inner join supplier
    on (nation.n_regionkey is not NULL)
where customer.c_nationkey is not NULL;
nl: What is the total duration of all transactions in regions where customers have a non-zero account balance?

sql:
select  
  part.p_container, 
  part.p_name, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  region.r_comment, 
  supplier.s_address
from 
  supplier
        inner join nation
        on (nation.n_name >= supplier.s_name)
      inner join region
      on (supplier.s_name <= supplier.s_name)
    inner join part
      inner join supplier
        inner join region
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_totalprice > orders.o_totalprice)
          inner join supplier
            inner join lineitem
              inner join orders
              on (lineitem.l_shipdate > lineitem.l_receiptdate)
            on (orders.o_shippriority <= orders.o_shippriority)
          on (orders.o_clerk = supplier.s_name )
        on (lineitem.l_discount > orders.o_totalprice)
      on (part.p_partkey < orders.o_custkey)
    on (supplier.s_name is not NULL)
where orders.o_custkey is not NULL;
nl: What are the details of parts, including their containers and names, along with supplier information, region comments, and addresses for customers who have placed large orders?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  region.r_regionkey
from 
  nation
          inner join partsupp
          on (partsupp.ps_supplycost = partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        inner join nation
          inner join customer
          on (nation.n_name = customer.c_phone )

  nation.n_regionkey,

from 
  region
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_totalprice >= orders.o_totalprice)
          inner join nation
          on (region.r_name > nation.n_name)
        inner join nation
          inner join orders
          on (orders.o_orderdate <= orders.o_orderdate)
        on (orders.o_custkey = nation.n_nationkey )
      inner join customer
        inner join part
        on (customer.c_phone = part.p_brand)
      on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)

    on (nation.n_regionkey is NULL)
where orders.o_orderpriority = part.p_brand

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(cast(null as pg_lsn) as pg_lsn)), 
  customer.c_address, 
  sum(
    cast(lineitem.l_discount as "numeric")), 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  orders.o_orderkey, 
  region.r_name, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as anyenum) as anyenum)), 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  region.r_comment
from 
  supplier
    inner join nation
              inner join region
              on (nation.n_regionkey < region.r_regionkey)
            inner join customer
              inner join orders
                inner join region
                on (orders.o_shippriority <= orders.o_orderkey)
              on (orders.o_orderstatus < customer.c_mktsegment)
            on (orders.o_orderkey <= customer.c_nationkey)
          inner join orders
          on (orders.o_totalprice >= orders.o_totalprice)
        inner join lineitem
            inner join customer
            on (lineitem.l_returnflag <= lineitem.l_linestatus)
          inner join region
            inner join region
            on (region.r_regionkey < region.r_regionkey)
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate < lineitem.l_receiptdate)
        on (orders.o_orderdate >= lineitem.l_commitdate)
      inner join part
      on (lineitem.l_extendedprice <= orders.o_totalprice)
    on (supplier.s_name = part.p_mfgr )
where lineitem.l_extendedprice >= customer.c_acctbal
limit 156;

from

            on (customer.c_nationkey = customer.c_custkey)
          inner join part
          on (part.p_partkey = customer.c_nationkey)
        inner join region
        on (part.p_retailprice <= part.p_retailprice)
      inner join supplier
          inner join lineitem
          on (supplier.s_acctbal = lineitem.l_quantity )
        inner join part
        on (lineitem.l_discount <= supplier.s_acctbal)
      on (lineitem.l_quantity = lineitem.l_quantity)
    inner join customer
        inner join part
        on (part.p_container <= part.p_brand)
      inner join region
      on (part.p_mfgr > region.r_name)
    on (lineitem.l_commitdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)

sql:
select  
  region.r_name
from 
  customer
        inner join nation
            inner join region
              inner join part
              on (part.p_brand <= region.r_name)
            on (part.p_retailprice = part.p_retailprice)
          inner join lineitem
          on (region.r_comment = lineitem.l_comment )
        on (customer.c_mktsegment = part.p_mfgr )
      inner join nation
          inner join lineitem
              inner join region
              on (lineitem.l_discount < lineitem.l_discount)
            inner join part
            on (lineitem.l_discount <= lineitem.l_quantity)
          on (lineitem.l_quantity >= lineitem.l_discount)
        inner join part
            inner join nation
              inner join lineitem
              on (nation.n_regionkey = lineitem.l_orderkey )
            on (part.p_retailprice < part.p_retailprice)
          inner join region
          on (lineitem.l_tax >= lineitem.l_tax)
        on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct = nation.n_name)
      on (region.r_regionkey < region.r_regionkey)
    inner join nation
        inner join part
        on (nation.n_name >= part.p_container)
      inner join region
      on (part.p_partkey = part.p_partkey)
    on (region.r_name = region.r_name )
where part.p_name is not NULL

            on (lineitem.l_commitdate < lineitem.l_commitdate)
          inner join orders
            inner join nation
              inner join part
              on (nation.n_nationkey < part.p_size)
            on (part.p_retailprice = orders.o_totalprice)
          on (orders.o_orderstatus >= part.p_mfgr)
        on (lineitem.l_partkey = customer.c_custkey )
      inner join lineitem
      on (lineitem.l_partkey = nation.n_regionkey)
    on (orders.o_orderpriority is NULL)
where lineitem.l_linenumber < lineitem.l_suppkey
limit 115;

  supplier.s_phone,

  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  supplier.s_acctbal,

  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  customer.c_acctbal, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  orders.o_shippriority, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost
from 
  nation
        inner join orders
        on (orders.o_clerk > orders.o_orderstatus)
      inner join nation
        inner join supplier
        on (supplier.s_acctbal = supplier.s_acctbal)
      on (supplier.s_acctbal = orders.o_totalprice)
    inner join partsupp
        inner join customer
        on (partsupp.ps_partkey = customer.c_custkey )
      inner join supplier
        inner join partsupp
          inner join customer
            inner join region
            on (customer.c_nationkey = customer.c_nationkey)
          on (partsupp.ps_supplycost >= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        on (supplier.s_nationkey > partsupp.ps_suppkey)
      on (partsupp.ps_supplycost < partsupp.ps_supplycost)
    on (partsupp.ps_availqty is NULL)
where customer.c_nationkey is not NULL

sql:
select  
  customer.c_custkey, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as timetz) as timetz)), 
  part.p_comment, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  customer.c_address
from 
  nation
          inner join part
            inner join region
              inner join customer
              on (region.r_regionkey <= region.r_regionkey)
            on (part.p_type = region.r_comment )
          on (part.p_retailprice = customer.c_acctbal)
        inner join supplier
            inner join nation
            on (nation.n_name < supplier.s_phone)
          inner join region
          on (supplier.s_name >= supplier.s_name)
        on (part.p_retailprice = supplier.s_acctbal)
      inner join customer
      on (part.p_size = customer.c_custkey )
    inner join nation
          inner join part
                inner join orders
                on (part.p_retailprice >= part.p_retailprice)
              inner join customer
                inner join nation
                  inner join partsupp
                  on (partsupp.ps_supplycost = partsupp.ps_supplycost)
                on (nation.n_nationkey <= customer.c_nationkey)
              on (partsupp.ps_suppkey <= orders.o_custkey)
            inner join part
            on (orders.o_orderdate > orders.o_orderdate)
          on (partsupp.ps_partkey = partsupp.ps_suppkey)
        inner join customer
        on (customer.c_address = customer.c_name )
      inner join part
      on (orders.o_orderpriority > nation.n_name)
    on (part.p_size is not NULL)
where nation.n_name >= customer.c_mktsegment
limit 157;

select

    cast(cast(null as oid) as oid)), 
  lineitem.l_shipdate
from 
  supplier
              inner join part
              on (supplier.s_nationkey < supplier.s_suppkey)
            inner join partsupp
              inner join supplier
                inner join orders
                on (orders.o_orderdate <= orders.o_orderdate)
              on (orders.o_orderdate <= orders.o_orderdate)
            on (supplier.s_nationkey = part.p_partkey)
          inner join part
          on (orders.o_orderdate <= orders.o_orderdate)
        inner join region
        on (supplier.s_name = region.r_name )
      inner join nation
          inner join lineitem
          on (nation.n_regionkey <= nation.n_regionkey)
        inner join supplier
          inner join region
            inner join partsupp
              inner join supplier
              on (supplier.s_nationkey >= partsupp.ps_partkey)
            on (supplier.s_name >= region.r_name)
          on (region.r_name < supplier.s_phone)
        on (supplier.s_suppkey > lineitem.l_orderkey)
      on (orders.o_clerk = nation.n_name )
    inner join lineitem
      inner join customer
      on (lineitem.l_returnflag >= lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
    on (part.p_mfgr > supplier.s_phone)
where region.r_regionkey is NULL

        inner join region
          inner join lineitem
            inner join orders
              inner join part
              on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
            on (lineitem.l_partkey = orders.o_orderkey )
          on (lineitem.l_discount = lineitem.l_discount)
        on (part.p_brand = part.p_mfgr )
      on (lineitem.l_linestatus >= part.p_mfgr)

select  
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  part.p_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey
from 
  partsupp
            inner join partsupp
            on (partsupp.ps_supplycost > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
          inner join nation
            inner join partsupp
              inner join partsupp
              on (partsupp.ps_partkey = partsupp.ps_availqty)
            on (partsupp.ps_supplycost < partsupp.ps_supplycost)
          on (nation.n_name <= nation.n_name)
        inner join supplier
        on (supplier.s_suppkey <= partsupp.ps_availqty)
      inner join orders
      on (partsupp.ps_suppkey = orders.o_orderkey )
    inner join nation
        inner join part
        on (part.p_size <= part.p_size)
      inner join supplier
        inner join part
        on (part.p_brand = part.p_brand)
      on (part.p_partkey <= part.p_size)
    on (orders.o_orderpriority <= supplier.s_phone)
where partsupp.ps_availqty <= partsupp.ps_availqty;

from 
  part
          inner join orders
          on (part.p_retailprice <= part.p_retailprice)

      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_totalprice > orders.o_totalprice)
    inner join lineitem
      inner join customer
        inner join orders
        on (orders.o_totalprice >= orders.o_totalprice)

              inner join customer
              on (nation.n_nationkey = customer.c_nationkey)
            on (customer.c_nationkey < nation.n_nationkey)
          inner join supplier
          on (customer.c_nationkey <= customer.c_nationkey)
        on (customer.c_nationkey = nation.n_nationkey)
      inner join customer
      on (supplier.s_acctbal <= supplier.s_acctbal)

        inner join partsupp
        on (partsupp.ps_suppkey = orders.o_custkey)

select

  supplier.s_nationkey
from 
  nation
        inner join lineitem
            inner join part
            on (part.p_retailprice >= lineitem.l_tax)
          inner join nation
                inner join lineitem
                on (lineitem.l_shipdate < lineitem.l_commitdate)
              inner join customer
              on (lineitem.l_orderkey <= customer.c_nationkey)
            inner join nation
            on (customer.c_nationkey < nation.n_regionkey)
          on (customer.c_mktsegment > lineitem.l_returnflag)
        on (part.p_container > customer.c_mktsegment)
      inner join part
        inner join nation
            inner join supplier
            on (supplier.s_phone < supplier.s_name)
          inner join nation
            inner join supplier
            on (supplier.s_name >= supplier.s_name)
          on (supplier.s_suppkey = nation.n_nationkey )
        on (nation.n_name < part.p_mfgr)
      on (nation.n_comment = nation.n_comment )
    inner join lineitem
      inner join part
      on (lineitem.l_commitdate < lineitem.l_shipdate)
    on (lineitem.l_quantity = lineitem.l_tax)
where lineitem.l_discount <= part.p_retailprice

  orders.o_orderstatus
from 
  part
      inner join supplier
            inner join supplier
              inner join orders
              on (orders.o_totalprice = orders.o_totalprice)
            on (supplier.s_suppkey = supplier.s_suppkey)
          inner join customer
            inner join region
              inner join supplier
                  inner join orders
                  on (supplier.s_acctbal > supplier.s_acctbal)
                inner join nation
                on (nation.n_name > orders.o_orderpriority)
              on (orders.o_totalprice <= orders.o_totalprice)
            on (orders.o_clerk > region.r_name)
          on (supplier.s_name = orders.o_orderstatus )
        inner join partsupp
          inner join orders
          on (partsupp.ps_partkey < orders.o_orderkey)
        on (region.r_regionkey = orders.o_orderkey )
      on (partsupp.ps_supplycost <= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
    inner join orders
        inner join supplier
          inner join region
            inner join supplier
            on (supplier.s_acctbal < supplier.s_acctbal)
          on (supplier.s_nationkey = supplier.s_nationkey)
        on (orders.o_totalprice >= supplier.s_acctbal)
      inner join part
          inner join orders
          on (orders.o_orderdate <= orders.o_orderdate)
        inner join nation
        on (part.p_brand >= nation.n_name)
      on (orders.o_clerk = orders.o_orderstatus )
    on (supplier.s_suppkey = supplier.s_suppkey )

  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as timetz) as timetz)), 
  customer.c_name, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  orders.o_comment, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  orders.o_orderstatus, 
  orders.o_clerk, 
  orders.o_orderpriority, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  orders.o_orderstatus, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  customer.c_mktsegment
from 
  orders
      inner join partsupp
        inner join partsupp
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_clerk <= orders.o_orderstatus)
          inner join region
          on (partsupp.ps_partkey >= orders.o_shippriority)
        on (partsupp.ps_supplycost >= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
      on (orders.o_orderpriority < region.r_name)
    inner join customer
      inner join lineitem
      on (lineitem.l_tax <= customer.c_acctbal)
    on (orders.o_custkey is NULL)
where partsupp.ps_comment is NULL;
nl: What are the order dates, total prices, supplier keys, region comments, part keys, and supply costs for orders with no returns, minimum shipment times, and specific market segments?

from

    inner join orders
        inner join lineitem

where partsupp.ps_supplycost >= lineitem.l_quantity;

sql:
select  
  region.r_name, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  supplier.s_phone
from 
  nation
      inner join customer
          inner join region
          on (customer.c_acctbal <= customer.c_acctbal)
        inner join supplier
        on (region.r_comment = supplier.s_address )
      on (supplier.s_phone <= supplier.s_phone)
    inner join region
        inner join lineitem
            inner join supplier
              inner join customer
              on (customer.c_custkey <= customer.c_nationkey)
            on (lineitem.l_extendedprice = supplier.s_acctbal )
          inner join orders
              inner join nation
                  inner join customer
                  on (customer.c_phone > customer.c_phone)
                inner join region
                on (region.r_name = customer.c_mktsegment)
              on (orders.o_orderstatus = nation.n_name )
            inner join supplier
            on (nation.n_name > nation.n_name)
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate < orders.o_orderdate)
        on (region.r_name = lineitem.l_returnflag )
      inner join part
        inner join customer
        on (part.p_retailprice < customer.c_acctbal)
      on (customer.c_custkey <= orders.o_shippriority)
    on (customer.c_custkey is NULL)
where part.p_brand is NULL
limit 153;

            inner join customer
            on (region.r_name >= customer.c_mktsegment)
          on (customer.c_custkey > customer.c_custkey)
        on (lineitem.l_quantity = lineitem.l_quantity)

sql:
select  
  min(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  supplier.s_acctbal
from 
  partsupp
      inner join orders
        inner join part
          inner join lineitem
            inner join supplier
              inner join part
              on (part.p_brand >= supplier.s_phone)
            on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
          on (part.p_container < lineitem.l_returnflag)
        on (supplier.s_acctbal >= lineitem.l_tax)
      on (part.p_brand = orders.o_clerk)
    inner join supplier
      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_totalprice = supplier.s_acctbal)
    on (partsupp.ps_availqty is not NULL)
where part.p_mfgr < part.p_mfgr;

sql:
select

  part.p_brand
from 
  customer
        inner join lineitem
        on (customer.c_comment = lineitem.l_comment )
      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
    inner join part
        inner join lineitem
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_orderpriority <= lineitem.l_linestatus)
          inner join supplier
          on (lineitem.l_extendedprice = lineitem.l_discount)
        on (part.p_partkey = orders.o_orderkey )
      inner join part
        inner join part
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_suppkey > part.p_size)
        on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
      on (lineitem.l_quantity < part.p_retailprice)
    on (orders.o_orderkey is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_suppkey is NULL

sql:
select  
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  customer.c_acctbal, 
  region.r_name, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  orders.o_comment, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  region.r_name, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost
from 
  customer
      inner join supplier
        inner join customer
            inner join region
            on (customer.c_acctbal <= customer.c_acctbal)
          inner join nation
              inner join partsupp
              on (nation.n_regionkey > partsupp.ps_partkey)
            inner join region
              inner join orders
              on (orders.o_orderstatus >= region.r_name)
            on (orders.o_totalprice >= orders.o_totalprice)
          on (orders.o_totalprice < partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        on (customer.c_custkey < region.r_regionkey)
      on (nation.n_regionkey <= customer.c_nationkey)
    inner join region
          inner join nation
            inner join customer
            on (nation.n_regionkey <= nation.n_regionkey)
          on (nation.n_name > customer.c_phone)
        inner join orders
          inner join partsupp
            inner join region
            on (partsupp.ps_suppkey = region.r_regionkey )
          on (orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate)
        on (orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate)
      inner join lineitem
      on (partsupp.ps_partkey = nation.n_nationkey)
    on (region.r_comment is NULL)
where orders.o_orderdate is NULL
limit 112;

sql:
select  
  min(
    cast(cast(null as timetz) as timetz)), 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  orders.o_orderstatus, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as oid) as oid)), 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as anyarray) as anyarray)), 
  orders.o_comment, 
  part.p_size, 
  part.p_comment, 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  customer.c_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  count(*), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as oid) as oid)), 
  customer.c_nationkey
from 
  orders
          inner join part
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_tax < lineitem.l_tax)
          on (orders.o_clerk = lineitem.l_returnflag )
        inner join orders
        on (orders.o_totalprice > orders.o_totalprice)
      inner join region
          inner join nation
          on (region.r_regionkey > nation.n_nationkey)
        inner join part
        on (part.p_retailprice = part.p_retailprice)
      on (part.p_retailprice = orders.o_totalprice)
    inner join partsupp
      inner join region
              inner join lineitem
              on (lineitem.l_quantity >= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_nationkey >= lineitem.l_linenumber)
          inner join partsupp
            inner join partsupp
              inner join lineitem
              on (lineitem.l_shipdate >= lineitem.l_commitdate)
            on (lineitem.l_extendedprice = lineitem.l_discount)
          on (lineitem.l_suppkey < partsupp.ps_suppkey)
        inner join nation
        on (nation.n_nationkey >= lineitem.l_orderkey)
      on (lineitem.l_tax > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
    on (lineitem.l_linestatus >= lineitem.l_returnflag)
where lineitem.l_commitdate >= lineitem.l_commitdate
limit 81;

      inner join partsupp

            on (customer.c_phone = customer.c_mktsegment)
          on (lineitem.l_extendedprice = partsupp.ps_supplycost )
        inner join region
        on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct > lineitem.l_linestatus)
      inner join nation
      on (lineitem.l_linenumber = partsupp.ps_partkey)
    on (region.r_regionkey >= customer.c_nationkey)
where customer.c_address is not NULL;

select distinct 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  customer.c_acctbal, 
  region.r_name, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  region.r_name, 
  region.r_comment, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8)), 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  nation.n_name, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as text) as text)), 
  nation.n_name, 
  orders.o_clerk, 
  nation.n_name, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  avg(
    cast(customer.c_acctbal as "numeric"))
from 
  nation
      inner join nation
      on (nation.n_nationkey < nation.n_regionkey)
    inner join region
        inner join part
        on (part.p_retailprice > part.p_retailprice)
      inner join orders
        inner join partsupp
              inner join customer
                inner join nation
                on (customer.c_phone = customer.c_mktsegment)
              on (nation.n_name < customer.c_mktsegment)
            inner join nation
            on (customer.c_mktsegment = customer.c_phone)
          inner join customer
            inner join nation
            on (customer.c_phone > customer.c_phone)
          on (customer.c_acctbal = customer.c_acctbal)
        on (customer.c_acctbal > customer.c_acctbal)
      on (orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate)
    on (partsupp.ps_suppkey is NULL)
where nation.n_name is not NULL;

select  
  region.r_regionkey, 
  part.p_container,

  part.p_partkey, 
  region.r_comment, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  nation.n_name, 
  orders.o_orderstatus, 
  supplier.s_suppkey
from 
  part
    inner join part
        inner join region
          inner join customer
            inner join supplier
            on (customer.c_phone < customer.c_mktsegment)
          on (customer.c_acctbal > supplier.s_acctbal)
        on (part.p_size > supplier.s_suppkey)
      inner join part
            inner join supplier
            on (part.p_size > supplier.s_nationkey)
          inner join orders
          on (part.p_mfgr < orders.o_orderpriority)
        inner join supplier
          inner join orders
              inner join nation
              on (orders.o_orderdate <= orders.o_orderdate)
            inner join nation
            on (nation.n_regionkey = orders.o_shippriority)
          on (supplier.s_nationkey = nation.n_regionkey)
        on (supplier.s_name = nation.n_name )
      on (supplier.s_suppkey <= customer.c_custkey)
    on (part.p_retailprice < part.p_retailprice)
where orders.o_orderdate is NULL
limit 108;

select  
  min(

  region.r_regionkey, 
  region.r_name, 
  supplier.s_nationkey
from 
  partsupp
      inner join supplier
        inner join nation
        on (supplier.s_phone >= nation.n_name)
      on (supplier.s_acctbal <= supplier.s_acctbal)
    inner join region
          inner join part
                inner join partsupp
                on (part.p_partkey >= part.p_partkey)
              inner join part
              on (part.p_container <= part.p_mfgr)
            inner join part
            on (part.p_partkey > part.p_size)
          on (part.p_mfgr <= region.r_name)
        inner join part
            inner join nation
            on (part.p_partkey < nation.n_regionkey)
          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_nationkey < supplier.s_suppkey)
        on (supplier.s_name = part.p_mfgr)
      inner join lineitem
          inner join customer
            inner join partsupp
            on (partsupp.ps_availqty < partsupp.ps_availqty)
          on (partsupp.ps_availqty < lineitem.l_suppkey)
        inner join region
        on (customer.c_nationkey <= partsupp.ps_availqty)
      on (part.p_retailprice <= part.p_retailprice)
    on (part.p_brand is NULL)
where region.r_name is not NULL

        inner join nation
        on (nation.n_nationkey >= lineitem.l_partkey)
      on (lineitem.l_commitdate = lineitem.l_shipdate )
    inner join supplier
              inner join lineitem
              on (lineitem.l_linestatus < lineitem.l_linestatus)
            inner join nation
            on (lineitem.l_quantity >= lineitem.l_tax)
          inner join nation
              inner join region
              on (region.r_name >= region.r_name)
            inner join partsupp
            on (region.r_name > region.r_name)
          on (lineitem.l_orderkey = nation.n_nationkey )
        inner join nation
        on (lineitem.l_extendedprice > supplier.s_acctbal)
      inner join partsupp
      on (partsupp.ps_supplycost > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
    on (supplier.s_comment is NULL)
where nation.n_name is NULL;
nl: What are the line status, available quantity, and phone number of suppliers in a specific nation, along with the maximum order quantity, shipping mode, and nation name, for orders that have not been shipped yet?

sql:
select

from

where partsupp.ps_suppkey is NULL

sql:
select  
  count(*)
from 
  nation
    inner join lineitem
      inner join orders
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_linenumber > orders.o_orderkey)
        inner join partsupp
          inner join partsupp
            inner join customer
            on (partsupp.ps_suppkey <= partsupp.ps_availqty)
          on (customer.c_acctbal < partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        on (customer.c_custkey <= customer.c_custkey)
      on (lineitem.l_tax > lineitem.l_quantity)
    on (nation.n_comment is not NULL)
where partsupp.ps_comment is NULL;
nl: What are the total counts of all orders that have a tax greater than the quantity, where the supplier's available quantity is less than or equal to the supply cost, and there is no comment for the part?

sql:
select  
  region.r_regionkey, 
  lineitem.l_tax, 
  lineitem.l_tax, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as timetz) as timetz)), 
  customer.c_address, 
  region.r_comment, 
  customer.c_address, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  region.r_name
from 
  partsupp
          inner join nation
          on (nation.n_name >= nation.n_name)
        inner join customer
              inner join customer
              on (customer.c_mktsegment >= customer.c_mktsegment)
            inner join supplier
                inner join region
                on (supplier.s_phone > region.r_name)
              inner join customer
              on (supplier.s_name = customer.c_phone )
            on (customer.c_acctbal > customer.c_acctbal)
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate < lineitem.l_shipdate)
        on (partsupp.ps_comment = customer.c_name )
      inner join region
      on (lineitem.l_receiptdate < lineitem.l_shipdate)
    inner join orders
          inner join part
            inner join region
            on (part.p_size = region.r_regionkey)
          on (orders.o_orderdate > orders.o_orderdate)
        inner join customer
        on (orders.o_clerk < customer.c_phone)
      inner join lineitem
      on (lineitem.l_discount >= orders.o_totalprice)
    on (partsupp.ps_suppkey is NULL)
where supplier.s_name is NULL;
nl: What are the region keys, tax rates, minimum times, addresses, comments, available quantities, and names for regions where there are no suppliers or customers?

  part.p_container
from

sql:
select  
  nation.n_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  region.r_name, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2))
from 
  part
          inner join supplier
              inner join partsupp
              on (supplier.s_acctbal = supplier.s_acctbal)
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_nationkey < partsupp.ps_partkey)
          on (part.p_name = customer.c_name )
        inner join customer
          inner join region
          on (region.r_regionkey > region.r_regionkey)
        on (partsupp.ps_partkey = customer.c_custkey )
      inner join partsupp
        inner join region
          inner join customer
          on (region.r_name = customer.c_phone )
        on (partsupp.ps_availqty < customer.c_nationkey)
      on (customer.c_mktsegment = customer.c_mktsegment)
    inner join nation
        inner join part
        on (part.p_retailprice < part.p_retailprice)
      inner join nation
      on (part.p_size = nation.n_nationkey )
    on (partsupp.ps_suppkey is not NULL)
where part.p_retailprice is not NULL;

sql:
select  
  min(
    cast(cast(null as "time") as "time"))
from 
  part
      inner join orders
        inner join nation
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_nationkey = customer.c_custkey)
          inner join orders
          on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
        on (orders.o_totalprice < orders.o_totalprice)
      on (part.p_comment = orders.o_comment )
    inner join nation
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_returnflag < lineitem.l_returnflag)
        inner join nation
          inner join lineitem
          on (nation.n_name = lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
        on (lineitem.l_shipdate > lineitem.l_commitdate)
      inner join region
          inner join partsupp
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_shipmode > lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
          on (lineitem.l_tax <= lineitem.l_discount)
        inner join customer
          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_suppkey < supplier.s_suppkey)
        on (lineitem.l_discount = lineitem.l_tax)
      on (lineitem.l_shipdate >= lineitem.l_commitdate)
    on (lineitem.l_discount is NULL)
where nation.n_comment is NULL
limit 104;

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "timestamp") as "timestamp")), 
  nation.n_name, 
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  part.p_retailprice, 
  part.p_partkey
from 
  nation
        inner join part
        on (nation.n_regionkey = part.p_size)
      inner join lineitem
      on (lineitem.l_shipdate < lineitem.l_shipdate)
    inner join nation
        inner join part
            inner join orders
              inner join region
              on (orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate)
            on (orders.o_shippriority < orders.o_orderkey)
          inner join nation
          on (orders.o_orderstatus >= part.p_brand)
        on (region.r_regionkey > nation.n_nationkey)
      inner join nation
      on (nation.n_nationkey = nation.n_nationkey )
    on (nation.n_nationkey is not NULL)
where nation.n_nationkey is not NULL
limit 85;

      inner join customer
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_custkey > customer.c_nationkey)
          inner join nation
            inner join customer
              inner join supplier
                inner join supplier

              on (customer.c_comment = supplier.s_address )

sql:

sql:
select  
  orders.o_comment, 
  orders.o_custkey, 
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  orders.o_custkey, 
  count(*),

        on (lineitem.l_linestatus >= lineitem.l_linestatus)

select

    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  customer.c_acctbal, 
  region.r_name, 
  lineitem.l_quantity, 
  orders.o_totalprice
from 
  customer
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_extendedprice <= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_name > supplier.s_phone)
        inner join lineitem
        on (customer.c_phone = lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
      inner join partsupp
        inner join region
            inner join partsupp
              inner join orders
                inner join customer
                on (orders.o_orderstatus = customer.c_phone )
              on (partsupp.ps_comment = customer.c_name )
            on (region.r_comment = customer.c_name )
          inner join supplier
          on (customer.c_acctbal < customer.c_acctbal)
        on (orders.o_orderdate <= orders.o_orderdate)
      on (orders.o_clerk >= lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
    inner join part
      inner join region
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_orderkey <= region.r_regionkey)
        inner join orders
        on (orders.o_orderkey < orders.o_shippriority)
      on (part.p_retailprice > lineitem.l_tax)
    on (customer.c_nationkey is NULL)
where orders.o_orderstatus is not NULL;

        inner join customer
